2508  SubstTemplateTemplateParmStorage *subst =
2509  TN.getAsSubstTemplateTemplateParm();
2510  mangleExistingSubstitution(subst->getReplacement());
2511  break;
2512  }
2513 
2514  case TemplateName::SubstTemplateTemplateParmPack: {
2515  // FIXME: not clear how to mangle this!
2516  // template <template <class U> class T...> class A {
2517  // template <class U...> void foo(decltype(T<U>::foo) x...);
2518  // };
2519  Out << "_SUBSTPACK_";
2520  break;
2521  }
2522  case TemplateName::UsingTemplate: {
2523  TemplateDecl *TD = TN.getAsTemplateDecl();
2524  assert(TD && !isa<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(TD));
2525  mangleSourceNameWithAbiTags(TD);
2526  break;
2527  }
2528  }
2529 
2530  // Note: we don't pass in the template name here. We are mangling the
2531  // original source-level template arguments, so we shouldn't consider
2532  // conversions to the corresponding template parameter.
2533  // FIXME: Other compilers mangle partially-resolved template arguments in
2534  // unresolved-qualifier-levels.
2535  mangleTemplateArgs(TemplateName(), TST->template_arguments());
2536  break;
2537  }
2538 
2539  case Type::InjectedClassName:
2540  mangleSourceNameWithAbiTags(
2541  cast<InjectedClassNameType>(Ty)->getDecl());
2542  break;
2543 
2544  case Type::DependentName:
2545  mangleSourceName(cast<DependentNameType>(Ty)->getIdentifier());
2546  break;
2547 
2548  case Type::DependentTemplateSpecialization: {
2549  const DependentTemplateSpecializationType *DTST =
2550  cast<DependentTemplateSpecializationType>(Ty);
2551  TemplateName Template = getASTContext().getDependentTemplateName(
2552  DTST->getQualifier(), DTST->getIdentifier());
2553  mangleSourceName(DTST->getIdentifier());
2554  mangleTemplateArgs(Template, DTST->template_arguments());
2555  break;
2556  }
2557 
2558  case Type::Using:
2559  return mangleUnresolvedTypeOrSimpleId(cast<UsingType>(Ty)->desugar(),
2560  Prefix);
2561  case Type::Elaborated:
2562  return mangleUnresolvedTypeOrSimpleId(
2563  cast<ElaboratedType>(Ty)->getNamedType(), Prefix);
2564  }
2565 
2566  return false;
2567 }
2568 
2569 void CXXNameMangler::mangleOperatorName(DeclarationName Name, unsigned Arity) {
2570  switch (Name.getNameKind()) {
2571  case DeclarationName::CXXConstructorName:
2572  case DeclarationName::CXXDestructorName:
2573  case DeclarationName::CXXDeductionGuideName:
2574  case DeclarationName::CXXUsingDirective:
2575  case DeclarationName::Identifier:
2576  case DeclarationName::ObjCMultiArgSelector:
2577  case DeclarationName::ObjCOneArgSelector:
2578  case DeclarationName::ObjCZeroArgSelector:
2579  llvm_unreachable("Not an operator name");
2580 
2581  case DeclarationName::CXXConversionFunctionName:
2582  // <operator-name> ::= cv <type> # (cast)
2583  Out << "cv";
2584  mangleType(Name.getCXXNameType());
2585  break;
2586 
2587  case DeclarationName::CXXLiteralOperatorName:
2588  Out << "li";
2589  mangleSourceName(Name.getCXXLiteralIdentifier());
2590  return;
2591 
2592  case DeclarationName::CXXOperatorName:
2593  mangleOperatorName(Name.getCXXOverloadedOperator(), Arity);
2594  break;
2595  }
2596 }
2597 
2598 void
2599 CXXNameMangler::mangleOperatorName(OverloadedOperatorKind OO, unsigned Arity) {
2600  switch (OO) {
2601  // <operator-name> ::= nw # new
2602  case OO_New: Out << "nw"; break;
2603  // ::= na # new[]
2604  case OO_Array_New: Out << "na"; break;
2605  // ::= dl # delete
2606  case OO_Delete: Out << "dl"; break;
2607  // ::= da # delete[]
2608  case OO_Array_Delete: Out << "da"; break;
2609  // ::= ps # + (unary)
2610  // ::= pl # + (binary or unknown)
2611  case OO_Plus:
2612  Out << (Arity == 1? "ps" : "pl"); break;
2613  // ::= ng # - (unary)
2614  // ::= mi # - (binary or unknown)
2615  case OO_Minus:
2616  Out << (Arity == 1? "ng" : "mi"); break;
2617  // ::= ad # & (unary)
2618  // ::= an # & (binary or unknown)
2619  case OO_Amp:
2620  Out << (Arity == 1? "ad" : "an"); break;
2621  // ::= de # * (unary)
2622  // ::= ml # * (binary or unknown)
2623  case OO_Star:
2624  // Use binary when unknown.
2625  Out << (Arity == 1? "de" : "ml"); break;
2626  // ::= co # ~
2627  case OO_Tilde: Out << "co"; break;
2628  // ::= dv # /
2629  case OO_Slash: Out << "dv"; break;
2630  // ::= rm # %
2631  case OO_Percent: Out << "rm"; break;
2632  // ::= or # |
2633  case OO_Pipe: Out << "or"; break;
2634  // ::= eo # ^
2635  case OO_Caret: Out << "eo"; break;
2636  // ::= aS # =
2637  case OO_Equal: Out << "aS"; break;
2638  // ::= pL # +=
2639  case OO_PlusEqual: Out << "pL"; break;
2640  // ::= mI # -=
2641  case OO_MinusEqual: Out << "mI"; break;
2642  // ::= mL # *=
2643  case OO_StarEqual: Out << "mL"; break;
2644  // ::= dV # /=
2645  case OO_SlashEqual: Out << "dV"; break;
2646  // ::= rM # %=
2647  case OO_PercentEqual: Out << "rM"; break;
2648  // ::= aN # &=
2649  case OO_AmpEqual: Out << "aN"; break;
2650  // ::= oR # |=
2651  case OO_PipeEqual: Out << "oR"; break;
2652  // ::= eO # ^=
2653  case OO_CaretEqual: Out << "eO"; break;
2654  // ::= ls # <<
2655  case OO_LessLess: Out << "ls"; break;
2656  // ::= rs # >>
2657  case OO_GreaterGreater: Out << "rs"; break;
2658  // ::= lS # <<=
2659  case OO_LessLessEqual: Out << "lS"; break;
2660  // ::= rS # >>=
2661  case OO_GreaterGreaterEqual: Out << "rS"; break;
2662  // ::= eq # ==
2663  case OO_EqualEqual: Out << "eq"; break;
2664  // ::= ne # !=
2665  case OO_ExclaimEqual: Out << "ne"; break;
2666  // ::= lt # <
2667  case OO_Less: Out << "lt"; break;
2668  // ::= gt # >
2669  case OO_Greater: Out << "gt"; break;
2670  // ::= le # <=
2671  case OO_LessEqual: Out << "le"; break;
2672  // ::= ge # >=
2673  case OO_GreaterEqual: Out << "ge"; break;
2674  // ::= nt # !
2675  case OO_Exclaim: Out << "nt"; break;
2676  // ::= aa # &&
2677  case OO_AmpAmp: Out << "aa"; break;
2678  // ::= oo # ||
2679  case OO_PipePipe: Out << "oo"; break;
2680  // ::= pp # ++
2681  case OO_PlusPlus: Out << "pp"; break;
2682  // ::= mm # --
2683  case OO_MinusMinus: Out << "mm"; break;
2684  // ::= cm # ,
2685  case OO_Comma: Out << "cm"; break;
2686  // ::= pm # ->*
2687  case OO_ArrowStar: Out << "pm"; break;
2688  // ::= pt # ->
2689  case OO_Arrow: Out << "pt"; break;
2690  // ::= cl # ()
2691  case OO_Call: Out << "cl"; break;
2692  // ::= ix # []
2693  case OO_Subscript: Out << "ix"; break;
2694 
2695  // ::= qu # ?
2696  // The conditional operator can't be overloaded, but we still handle it when
2697  // mangling expressions.
2698  case OO_Conditional: Out << "qu"; break;
2699  // Proposal on cxx-abi-dev, 2015-10-21.
2700  // ::= aw # co_await
2701  case OO_Coawait: Out << "aw"; break;
2702  // Proposed in cxx-abi github issue 43.
2703  // ::= ss # <=>
2704  case OO_Spaceship: Out << "ss"; break;
2705 
2706  case OO_None:
2707  case NUM_OVERLOADED_OPERATORS:
2708  llvm_unreachable("Not an overloaded operator");
2709  }
2710 }
2711 
2712 void CXXNameMangler::mangleQualifiers(Qualifiers Quals, const DependentAddressSpaceType *DAST) {
2713  // Vendor qualifiers come first and if they are order-insensitive they must
2714  // be emitted in reversed alphabetical order, see Itanium ABI 5.1.5.
2715 
2716  // <type> ::= U <addrspace-expr>
2717  if (DAST) {
2718  Out << "U2ASI";
2719  mangleExpression(DAST->getAddrSpaceExpr());
2720  Out << "E";
2721  }
2722 
2723  // Address space qualifiers start with an ordinary letter.
2724  if (Quals.hasAddressSpace()) {
2725  // Address space extension:
2726  //
2727  // <type> ::= U <target-addrspace>
2728  // <type> ::= U <OpenCL-addrspace>
2729  // <type> ::= U <CUDA-addrspace>
2730 
2731  SmallString<64> ASString;
2732  LangAS AS = Quals.getAddressSpace();
2733 
2734  if (Context.getASTContext().addressSpaceMapManglingFor(AS)) {
2735  // <target-addrspace> ::= "AS" <address-space-number>
2736  unsigned TargetAS = Context.getASTContext().getTargetAddressSpace(AS);
2737  if (TargetAS != 0 ||
2738  Context.getASTContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::Default) != 0)
2739  ASString = "AS" + llvm::utostr(TargetAS);
2740  } else {
2741  switch (AS) {
2742  default: llvm_unreachable("Not a language specific address space");
2743  // <OpenCL-addrspace> ::= "CL" [ "global" | "local" | "constant" |
2744  // "private"| "generic" | "device" |
2745  // "host" ]
2746  case LangAS::opencl_global:
2747  ASString = "CLglobal";
2748  break;
2749  case LangAS::opencl_global_device:
2750  ASString = "CLdevice";
2751  break;
2752  case LangAS::opencl_global_host:
2753  ASString = "CLhost";
2754  break;
2755  case LangAS::opencl_local:
2756  ASString = "CLlocal";
2757  break;
2758  case LangAS::opencl_constant:
2759  ASString = "CLconstant";
2760  break;
2761  case LangAS::opencl_private:
2762  ASString = "CLprivate";
2763  break;
2764  case LangAS::opencl_generic:
2765  ASString = "CLgeneric";
2766  break;
2767  // <SYCL-addrspace> ::= "SY" [ "global" | "local" | "private" |
2768  // "device" | "host" ]
2769  case LangAS::sycl_global:
2770  ASString = "SYglobal";
2771  break;
2772  case LangAS::sycl_global_device:
2773  ASString = "SYglobaldevice";
2774  break;
2775  case LangAS::sycl_global_host:
2776  ASString = "SYglobalhost";
2777  break;
2778  case LangAS::sycl_local:
2779  ASString = "SYlocal";
2780  break;
2781  case LangAS::sycl_private:
2782  ASString = "SYprivate";
2783  break;
2784  // <CUDA-addrspace> ::= "CU" [ "device" | "constant" | "shared" ]
2785  case LangAS::cuda_device:
2786  ASString = "CUdevice";
2787  break;
2788  case LangAS::cuda_constant:
2789  ASString = "CUconstant";
2790  break;
2791  case LangAS::cuda_shared:
2792  ASString = "CUshared";
2793  break;
2794  // <ptrsize-addrspace> ::= [ "ptr32_sptr" | "ptr32_uptr" | "ptr64" ]
2795  case LangAS::ptr32_sptr:
2796  ASString = "ptr32_sptr";
2797  break;
2798  case LangAS::ptr32_uptr:
2799  ASString = "ptr32_uptr";
2800  break;
2801  case LangAS::ptr64:
2802  ASString = "ptr64";
2803  break;
2804  }
2805  }
2806  if (!ASString.empty())
2807  mangleVendorQualifier(ASString);
2808  }
2809 
2810  // The ARC ownership qualifiers start with underscores.
2811  // Objective-C ARC Extension:
2812  //
2813  // <type> ::= U "__strong"
2814  // <type> ::= U "__weak"
2815  // <type> ::= U "__autoreleasing"
2816  //
2817  // Note: we emit __weak first to preserve the order as
2818  // required by the Itanium ABI.
2819  if (Quals.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_Weak)
2820  mangleVendorQualifier("__weak");
2821 
2822  // __unaligned (from -fms-extensions)
2823  if (Quals.hasUnaligned())
2824  mangleVendorQualifier("__unaligned");
2825 
2826  // Remaining ARC ownership qualifiers.
2827  switch (Quals.getObjCLifetime()) {
2828  case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
2829  break;
2830 
2831  case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
2832  // Do nothing as we already handled this case above.
2833  break;
2834 
2835  case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
2836  mangleVendorQualifier("__strong");
2837  break;
2838 
2839  case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
2840  mangleVendorQualifier("__autoreleasing");
2841  break;
2842 
2843  case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
2844  // The __unsafe_unretained qualifier is *not* mangled, so that
2845  // __unsafe_unretained types in ARC produce the same manglings as the
2846  // equivalent (but, naturally, unqualified) types in non-ARC, providing
2847  // better ABI compatibility.
2848  //
2849  // It's safe to do this because unqualified 'id' won't show up
2850  // in any type signatures that need to be mangled.
2851  break;
2852  }
2853 
2854  // <CV-qualifiers> ::= [r] [V] [K] # restrict (C99), volatile, const
2855  if (Quals.hasRestrict())
2856  Out << 'r';
2857  if (Quals.hasVolatile())
2858  Out << 'V';
2859  if (Quals.hasConst())
2860  Out << 'K';
2861 }
2862 
2863 void CXXNameMangler::mangleVendorQualifier(StringRef name) {
2864  Out << 'U' << name.size() << name;
2865 }
2866 
2867 void CXXNameMangler::mangleRefQualifier(RefQualifierKind RefQualifier) {
2868  // <ref-qualifier> ::= R # lvalue reference
2869  // ::= O # rvalue-reference
2870  switch (RefQualifier) {
2871  case RQ_None:
2872  break;
2873 
2874  case RQ_LValue:
2875  Out << 'R';
2876  break;
2877 
2878  case RQ_RValue:
2879  Out << 'O';
2880  break;
2881  }
2882 }
2883 
2884 void CXXNameMangler::mangleObjCMethodName(const ObjCMethodDecl *MD) {
2885  Context.mangleObjCMethodNameAsSourceName(MD, Out);
2886 }
2887 
2888 static bool isTypeSubstitutable(Qualifiers Quals, const Type *Ty,
2889  ASTContext &Ctx) {
2890  if (Quals)
2891  return true;
2892  if (Ty->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::ObjCSel))
2893  return true;
2894  if (Ty->isOpenCLSpecificType())
2895  return true;
2896  // From Clang 18.0 we correctly treat SVE types as substitution candidates.
2897  if (Ty->isSVESizelessBuiltinType() &&
2898  Ctx.getLangOpts().getClangABICompat() > LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver17)
2899  return true;
2900  if (Ty->isBuiltinType())
2901  return false;
2902  // Through to Clang 6.0, we accidentally treated undeduced auto types as
2903  // substitution candidates.
2904  if (Ctx.getLangOpts().getClangABICompat() > LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver6 &&
2905  isa<AutoType>(Ty))
2906  return false;
2907  // A placeholder type for class template deduction is substitutable with
2908  // its corresponding template name; this is handled specially when mangling
2909  // the type.
2910  if (auto *DeducedTST = Ty->getAs<DeducedTemplateSpecializationType>())
2911  if (DeducedTST->getDeducedType().isNull())
2912  return false;
2913  return true;
2914 }
2915 
2916 void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(QualType T) {
2917  // If our type is instantiation-dependent but not dependent, we mangle
2918  // it as it was written in the source, removing any top-level sugar.
2919  // Otherwise, use the canonical type.
2920  //
2921  // FIXME: This is an approximation of the instantiation-dependent name
2922  // mangling rules, since we should really be using the type as written and
2923  // augmented via semantic analysis (i.e., with implicit conversions and
2924  // default template arguments) for any instantiation-dependent type.
2925  // Unfortunately, that requires several changes to our AST:
2926  // - Instantiation-dependent TemplateSpecializationTypes will need to be
2927  // uniqued, so that we can handle substitutions properly
2928  // - Default template arguments will need to be represented in the
2929  // TemplateSpecializationType, since they need to be mangled even though
2930  // they aren't written.
2931  // - Conversions on non-type template arguments need to be expressed, since
2932  // they can affect the mangling of sizeof/alignof.
2933  //
2934  // FIXME: This is wrong when mapping to the canonical type for a dependent
2935  // type discards instantiation-dependent portions of the type, such as for:
2936  //
2937  // template<typename T, int N> void f(T (&)[sizeof(N)]);
2938  // template<typename T> void f(T() throw(typename T::type)); (pre-C++17)
2939  //
2940  // It's also wrong in the opposite direction when instantiation-dependent,
2941  // canonically-equivalent types differ in some irrelevant portion of inner
2942  // type sugar. In such cases, we fail to form correct substitutions, eg:
2943  //
2944  // template<int N> void f(A<sizeof(N)> *, A<sizeof(N)> (*));
2945  //
2946  // We should instead canonicalize the non-instantiation-dependent parts,
2947  // regardless of whether the type as a whole is dependent or instantiation
2948  // dependent.
2949  if (!T->isInstantiationDependentType() || T->isDependentType())
2950  T = T.getCanonicalType();
2951  else {
2952  // Desugar any types that are purely sugar.
2953  do {
2954  // Don't desugar through template specialization types that aren't
2955  // type aliases. We need to mangle the template arguments as written.
2956  if (const TemplateSpecializationType *TST
2957  = dyn_cast<TemplateSpecializationType>(T))
2958  if (!TST->isTypeAlias())
2959  break;
2960 
2961  // FIXME: We presumably shouldn't strip off ElaboratedTypes with
2962  // instantation-dependent qualifiers. See
2963  // https://github.com/itanium-cxx-abi/cxx-abi/issues/114.
2964 
2965  QualType Desugared
2966  = T.getSingleStepDesugaredType(Context.getASTContext());
2967  if (Desugared == T)
2968  break;
2969 
2970  T = Desugared;
2971  } while (true);
2972  }
2973  SplitQualType split = T.split();
2974  Qualifiers quals = split.Quals;
2975  const Type *ty = split.Ty;
2976 
2977  bool isSubstitutable =
2978  isTypeSubstitutable(quals, ty, Context.getASTContext());
2979  if (isSubstitutable && mangleSubstitution(T))
2980  return;
2981 
2982  // If we're mangling a qualified array type, push the qualifiers to
2983  // the element type.
2984  if (quals && isa<ArrayType>(T)) {
2985  ty = Context.getASTContext().getAsArrayType(T);
2986  quals = Qualifiers();
2987 
2988  // Note that we don't update T: we want to add the
2989  // substitution at the original type.
2990  }
2991 
2992  if (quals || ty->isDependentAddressSpaceType()) {
2993  if (const DependentAddressSpaceType *DAST =
2994  dyn_cast<DependentAddressSpaceType>(ty)) {
2995  SplitQualType splitDAST = DAST->getPointeeType().split();
2996  mangleQualifiers(splitDAST.Quals, DAST);
2997  mangleType(QualType(splitDAST.Ty, 0));
2998  } else {
2999  mangleQualifiers(quals);
3000 
3001  // Recurse: even if the qualified type isn't yet substitutable,
3002  // the unqualified type might be.
3003  mangleType(QualType(ty, 0));
3004  }
3005  } else {
3006  switch (ty->getTypeClass()) {
3007 #define ABSTRACT_TYPE(CLASS, PARENT)
3008 #define NON_CANONICAL_TYPE(CLASS, PARENT) \
3009  case Type::CLASS: \
3010  llvm_unreachable("can't mangle non-canonical type " #CLASS "Type"); \
3011  return;
3012 #define TYPE(CLASS, PARENT) \
3013  case Type::CLASS: \
3014  mangleType(static_cast<const CLASS##Type*>(ty)); \
3015  break;
3016 #include "clang/AST/TypeNodes.inc"
3017  }
3018  }
3019 
3020  // Add the substitution.
3021  if (isSubstitutable)
3022  addSubstitution(T);
3023 }
3024 
3025 void CXXNameMangler::mangleNameOrStandardSubstitution(const NamedDecl *ND) {
3026  if (!mangleStandardSubstitution(ND))
3027  mangleName(ND);
3028 }

3030 void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const BuiltinType *T) {
3031  // <type> ::= <builtin-type>
3032  // <builtin-type> ::= v # void
3033  // ::= w # wchar_t
3034  // ::= b # bool
3035  // ::= c # char
3036  // ::= a # signed char
3037  // ::= h # unsigned char
3038  // ::= s # short
3039  // ::= t # unsigned short
3040  // ::= i # int
3041  // ::= j # unsigned int
3042  // ::= l # long
3043  // ::= m # unsigned long
3044  // ::= x # long long, __int64
3045  // ::= y # unsigned long long, __int64
3046  // ::= n # __int128
3047  // ::= o # unsigned __int128
3048  // ::= f # float
3049  // ::= d # double
3050  // ::= e # long double, __float80
3051  // ::= g # __float128
3052  // ::= g # __ibm128
3053  // UNSUPPORTED: ::= Dd # IEEE 754r decimal floating point (64 bits)
3054  // UNSUPPORTED: ::= De # IEEE 754r decimal floating point (128 bits)
3055  // UNSUPPORTED: ::= Df # IEEE 754r decimal floating point (32 bits)
3056  // ::= Dh # IEEE 754r half-precision floating point (16 bits)
3057  // ::= DF <number> _ # ISO/IEC TS 18661 binary floating point type _FloatN (N bits);
3058  // ::= Di # char32_t
3059  // ::= Ds # char16_t
3060  // ::= Dn # std::nullptr_t (i.e., decltype(nullptr))
3061  // ::= [DS] DA # N1169 fixed-point [_Sat] T _Accum
3062  // ::= [DS] DR # N1169 fixed-point [_Sat] T _Fract
3063  // ::= u <source-name> # vendor extended type
3064  //
3065  // <fixed-point-size>
3066  // ::= s # short
3067  // ::= t # unsigned short
3068  // ::= i # plain
3069  // ::= j # unsigned
3070  // ::= l # long
3071  // ::= m # unsigned long
3072  std::string type_name;
3073  // Normalize integer types as vendor extended types:
3074  // u<length>i<type size>
3075  // u<length>u<type size>
3076  if (NormalizeIntegers && T->isInteger()) {
3077  if (T->isSignedInteger()) {
3078  switch (getASTContext().getTypeSize(T)) {
3079  case 8:
3080  // Pick a representative for each integer size in the substitution
3081  // dictionary. (Its actual defined size is not relevant.)
3082  if (mangleSubstitution(BuiltinType::SChar))
3083  break;
3084  Out << "u2i8";
3085  addSubstitution(BuiltinType::SChar);
3086  break;
3087  case 16:
3088  if (mangleSubstitution(BuiltinType::Short))
3089  break;
3090  Out << "u3i16";
3091  addSubstitution(BuiltinType::Short);
3092  break;
3093  case 32:
3094  if (mangleSubstitution(BuiltinType::Int))
3095  break;
3096  Out << "u3i32";
3097  addSubstitution(BuiltinType::Int);
3098  break;
3099  case 64:
3100  if (mangleSubstitution(BuiltinType::Long))
3101  break;
3102  Out << "u3i64";
3103  addSubstitution(BuiltinType::Long);
3104  break;
3105  case 128:
3106  if (mangleSubstitution(BuiltinType::Int128))
3107  break;
3108  Out << "u4i128";
3109  addSubstitution(BuiltinType::Int128);
3110  break;
3111  default:
3112  llvm_unreachable("Unknown integer size for normalization");
3113  }
3114  } else {
3115  switch (getASTContext().getTypeSize(T)) {
3116  case 8:
3117  if (mangleSubstitution(BuiltinType::UChar))
3118  break;
3119  Out << "u2u8";
3120  addSubstitution(BuiltinType::UChar);
3121  break;
3122  case 16:
3123  if (mangleSubstitution(BuiltinType::UShort))
3124  break;
3125  Out << "u3u16";
3126  addSubstitution(BuiltinType::UShort);
3127  break;
3128  case 32:
3129  if (mangleSubstitution(BuiltinType::UInt))
3130  break;
3131  Out << "u3u32";
3132  addSubstitution(BuiltinType::UInt);
3133  break;
3134  case 64:
3135  if (mangleSubstitution(BuiltinType::ULong))
3136  break;
3137  Out << "u3u64";
3138  addSubstitution(BuiltinType::ULong);
3139  break;
3140  case 128:
3141  if (mangleSubstitution(BuiltinType::UInt128))
3142  break;
3143  Out << "u4u128";
3144  addSubstitution(BuiltinType::UInt128);
3145  break;
3146  default:
3147  llvm_unreachable("Unknown integer size for normalization");
3148  }
3149  }
3150  return;
3151  }
3152  switch (T->getKind()) {
3153  case BuiltinType::Void:
3154  Out << 'v';
3155  break;
3156  case BuiltinType::Bool:
3157  Out << 'b';
3158  break;
3159  case BuiltinType::Char_U:
3160  case BuiltinType::Char_S:

3437 StringRef CXXNameMangler::getCallingConvQualifierName(CallingConv CC) {
3438  switch (CC) {
3439  case CC_C:
3440  return "";
3441 
3442  case CC_X86VectorCall:
3443  case CC_X86Pascal:
3444  case CC_X86RegCall:
3445  case CC_AAPCS:
3446  case CC_AAPCS_VFP:
3447  case CC_AArch64VectorCall:
3448  case CC_AArch64SVEPCS:
3449  case CC_AMDGPUKernelCall:
3450  case CC_IntelOclBicc:
3451  case CC_SpirFunction:
3452  case CC_OpenCLKernel:
3453  case CC_PreserveMost:
3454  case CC_PreserveAll:
3455  case CC_M68kRTD:
3456  case CC_PreserveNone:
3457  case CC_RISCVVectorCall:
3458  // FIXME: we should be mangling all of the above.
3459  return "";
3460 
3461  case CC_X86ThisCall:
3462  // FIXME: To match mingw GCC, thiscall should only be mangled in when it is
3463  // used explicitly. At this point, we don't have that much information in
3464  // the AST, since clang tends to bake the convention into the canonical
3465  // function type. thiscall only rarely used explicitly, so don't mangle it
3466  // for now.
3467  return "";
3468 
3469  case CC_X86StdCall:
3470  return "stdcall";
3471  case CC_X86FastCall:
3472  return "fastcall";
3473  case CC_X86_64SysV:
3474  return "sysv_abi";
3475  case CC_Win64:
3476  return "ms_abi";
3477  case CC_Swift:
3478  return "swiftcall";
3479  case CC_SwiftAsync:
3480  return "swiftasynccall";
3481  }
3482  llvm_unreachable("bad calling convention");
3483 }

3485 void CXXNameMangler::mangleExtFunctionInfo(const FunctionType *T) {
3486  // Fast path.
3487  if (T->getExtInfo() == FunctionType::ExtInfo())
3488  return;
3489 
3490  // Vendor-specific qualifiers are emitted in reverse alphabetical order.
3491  // This will get more complicated in the future if we mangle other
3492  // things here; but for now, since we mangle ns_returns_retained as
3493  // a qualifier on the result type, we can get away with this:
3494  StringRef CCQualifier = getCallingConvQualifierName(T->getExtInfo().getCC());
3495  if (!CCQualifier.empty())
3496  mangleVendorQualifier(CCQualifier);
3497 
3498  // FIXME: regparm
3499  // FIXME: noreturn
3500 }
3501 
3502 void
3503 CXXNameMangler::mangleExtParameterInfo(FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo PI) {
3504  // Vendor-specific qualifiers are emitted in reverse alphabetical order.
3505 
3506  // Note that these are *not* substitution candidates. Demanglers might
3507  // have trouble with this if the parameter type is fully substituted.
3508 
3509  switch (PI.getABI()) {
3510  case ParameterABI::Ordinary:
3511  break;
3512 
3513  // All of these start with "swift", so they come before "ns_consumed".
3514  case ParameterABI::SwiftContext:
3515  case ParameterABI::SwiftAsyncContext:
3516  case ParameterABI::SwiftErrorResult:
3517  case ParameterABI::SwiftIndirectResult:
3518  mangleVendorQualifier(getParameterABISpelling(PI.getABI()));
3519  break;
3520  }
3521 
3522  if (PI.isConsumed())
3523  mangleVendorQualifier("ns_consumed");
3524 
3525  if (PI.isNoEscape())
3526  mangleVendorQualifier("noescape");
3527 }

3529 // <type> ::= <function-type>
3530 // <function-type> ::= [<CV-qualifiers>] F [Y]
3531 // <bare-function-type> [<ref-qualifier>] E
3532 void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const FunctionProtoType *T) {
3533  mangleExtFunctionInfo(T);
3534 
3535  // Mangle CV-qualifiers, if present. These are 'this' qualifiers,
3536  // e.g. "const" in "int (A::*)() const".
3537  mangleQualifiers(T->getMethodQuals());
3538 
3539  // Mangle instantiation-dependent exception-specification, if present,
3540  // per cxx-abi-dev proposal on 2016-10-11.
3541  if (T->hasInstantiationDependentExceptionSpec()) {
3542  if (isComputedNoexcept(T->getExceptionSpecType())) {
3543  Out << "DO";
3544  mangleExpression(T->getNoexceptExpr());
3545  Out << "E";
3546  } else {
3547  assert(T->getExceptionSpecType() == EST_Dynamic);
3548  Out << "Dw";
3549  for (auto ExceptTy : T->exceptions())
3550  mangleType(ExceptTy);
3551  Out << "E";
3552  }
3553  } else if (T->isNothrow()) {
3554  Out << "Do";
3555  }
3556 
3557  Out << 'F';
3558 
3559  // FIXME: We don't have enough information in the AST to produce the 'Y'
3560  // encoding for extern "C" function types.
3561  mangleBareFunctionType(T, /*MangleReturnType=*/true);
3562 
3563  // Mangle the ref-qualifier, if present.
3564  mangleRefQualifier(T->getRefQualifier());
3565 
3566  Out << 'E';
3567 }
3568 
3569 void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const FunctionNoProtoType *T) {
3570  // Function types without prototypes can arise when mangling a function type
3571  // within an overloadable function in C. We mangle these as the absence of any
3572  // parameter types (not even an empty parameter list).
3573  Out << 'F';
3574 
3575  FunctionTypeDepthState saved = FunctionTypeDepth.push();
3576 
3577  FunctionTypeDepth.enterResultType();
3578  mangleType(T->getReturnType());
3579  FunctionTypeDepth.leaveResultType();
3580 
3581  FunctionTypeDepth.pop(saved);
3582  Out << 'E';
3583 }
3584 
3585 void CXXNameMangler::mangleBareFunctionType(const FunctionProtoType *Proto,
3586  bool MangleReturnType,
3587  const FunctionDecl *FD) {
3588  // Record that we're in a function type. See mangleFunctionParam
3589  // for details on what we're trying to achieve here.
3590  FunctionTypeDepthState saved = FunctionTypeDepth.push();
3591 
3592  // <bare-function-type> ::= <signature type>+
3593  if (MangleReturnType) {
3594  FunctionTypeDepth.enterResultType();
3595 
3596  // Mangle ns_returns_retained as an order-sensitive qualifier here.
3597  if (Proto->getExtInfo().getProducesResult() && FD == nullptr)
3598  mangleVendorQualifier("ns_returns_retained");
3599 
3600  // Mangle the return type without any direct ARC ownership qualifiers.
3601  QualType ReturnTy = Proto->getReturnType();
3602  if (ReturnTy.getObjCLifetime()) {
3603  auto SplitReturnTy = ReturnTy.split();
3604  SplitReturnTy.Quals.removeObjCLifetime();
3605  ReturnTy = getASTContext().getQualifiedType(SplitReturnTy);
3606  }
3607  mangleType(ReturnTy);
3608 
3609  FunctionTypeDepth.leaveResultType();
3610  }
3611 
3612  if (Proto->getNumParams() == 0 && !Proto->isVariadic()) {
3613  // <builtin-type> ::= v # void
3614  Out << 'v';
3615  } else {
3616  assert(!FD || FD->getNumParams() == Proto->getNumParams());
3617  for (unsigned I = 0, E = Proto->getNumParams(); I != E; ++I) {
3618  // Mangle extended parameter info as order-sensitive qualifiers here.
3619  if (Proto->hasExtParameterInfos() && FD == nullptr) {
3620  mangleExtParameterInfo(Proto->getExtParameterInfo(I));
3621  }
3622 
3623  // Mangle the type.
3624  QualType ParamTy = Proto->getParamType(I);
3625  mangleType(Context.getASTContext().getSignatureParameterType(ParamTy));
3626 
3627  if (FD) {
3628  if (auto *Attr = FD->getParamDecl(I)->getAttr<PassObjectSizeAttr>()) {
3629  // Attr can only take 1 character, so we can hardcode the length
3630  // below.
3631  assert(Attr->getType() <= 9 && Attr->getType() >= 0);
3632  if (Attr->isDynamic())
3633  Out << "U25pass_dynamic_object_size" << Attr->getType();
3634  else
3635  Out << "U17pass_object_size" << Attr->getType();
3636  }
3637  }
3638  }
3639 
3640  // <builtin-type> ::= z # ellipsis
3641  if (Proto->isVariadic())
3642  Out << 'z';
3643  }
3644 
3645  if (FD) {
3646  FunctionTypeDepth.enterResultType();
3647  mangleRequiresClause(FD->getTrailingRequiresClause());
3648  }
3649 
3650  FunctionTypeDepth.pop(saved);
3651 }
3652

3655 void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const UnresolvedUsingType *T) {
3656  mangleName(T->getDecl());
3657 }

3701 // <type> ::= <pointer-to-member-type>
3702 // <pointer-to-member-type> ::= M <class type> <member type>
3703 void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const MemberPointerType *T) {
3704  Out << 'M';
3705  mangleType(QualType(T->getClass(), 0));
3706  QualType PointeeType = T->getPointeeType();
3707  if (const FunctionProtoType *FPT = dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(PointeeType)) {
3708  mangleType(FPT);
3709 
3710  // Itanium C++ ABI 5.1.8:
3711  //
3712  // The type of a non-static member function is considered to be different,
3713  // for the purposes of substitution, from the type of a namespace-scope or
3714  // static member function whose type appears similar. The types of two
3715  // non-static member functions are considered to be different, for the
3716  // purposes of substitution, if the functions are members of different
3717  // classes. In other words, for the purposes of substitution, the class of
3718  // which the function is a member is considered part of the type of
3719  // function.
3720 
3721  // Given that we already substitute member function pointers as a
3722  // whole, the net effect of this rule is just to unconditionally
3723  // suppress substitution on the function type in a member pointer.
3724  // We increment the SeqID here to emulate adding an entry to the
3725  // substitution table.
3726  ++SeqID;
3727  } else
3728  mangleType(PointeeType);
3729 }

3773 // ARM's ABI for Neon vector types specifies that they should be mangled as
3774 // if they are structs (to match ARM's initial implementation). The
3775 // vector type must be one of the special types predefined by ARM.
3776 void CXXNameMangler::mangleNeonVectorType(const VectorType *T) {
3777  QualType EltType = T->getElementType();
3778  assert(EltType->isBuiltinType() && "Neon vector element not a BuiltinType");
3779  const char *EltName = nullptr;
3780  if (T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::NeonPoly) {
3781  switch (cast<BuiltinType>(EltType)->getKind()) {
3782  case BuiltinType::SChar:
3783  case BuiltinType::UChar:
3784  EltName = "poly8_t";
3785  break;
3786  case BuiltinType::Short:
3787  case BuiltinType::UShort:
3788  EltName = "poly16_t";
3789  break;
3790  case BuiltinType::LongLong:
3791  case BuiltinType::ULongLong:
3792  EltName = "poly64_t";
3793  break;
3794  default: llvm_unreachable("unexpected Neon polynomial vector element type");
3795  }
3796  } else {
3797  switch (cast<BuiltinType>(EltType)->getKind()) {
3798  case BuiltinType::SChar: EltName = "int8_t"; break;
3799  case BuiltinType::UChar: EltName = "uint8_t"; break;
3800  case BuiltinType::Short: EltName = "int16_t"; break;
3801  case BuiltinType::UShort: EltName = "uint16_t"; break;
3802  case BuiltinType::Int: EltName = "int32_t"; break;
3803  case BuiltinType::UInt: EltName = "uint32_t"; break;
3804  case BuiltinType::LongLong: EltName = "int64_t"; break;
3805  case BuiltinType::ULongLong: EltName = "uint64_t"; break;
3806  case BuiltinType::Double: EltName = "float64_t"; break;
3807  case BuiltinType::Float: EltName = "float32_t"; break;
3808  case BuiltinType::Half: EltName = "float16_t"; break;
3809  case BuiltinType::BFloat16: EltName = "bfloat16_t"; break;
3810  default:
3811  llvm_unreachable("unexpected Neon vector element type");
3812  }
3813  }
3814  const char *BaseName = nullptr;
3815  unsigned BitSize = (T->getNumElements() *
3816  getASTContext().getTypeSize(EltType));
3817  if (BitSize == 64)
3818  BaseName = "__simd64_";
3819  else {
3820  assert(BitSize == 128 && "Neon vector type not 64 or 128 bits");
3821  BaseName = "__simd128_";
3822  }
3823  Out << strlen(BaseName) + strlen(EltName);
3824  Out << BaseName << EltName;
3825 }

3827 void CXXNameMangler::mangleNeonVectorType(const DependentVectorType *T) {
3828  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags = Context.getDiags();
3829  unsigned DiagID = Diags.getCustomDiagID(
3830  DiagnosticsEngine::Error,
3831  "cannot mangle this dependent neon vector type yet");
3832  Diags.Report(T->getAttributeLoc(), DiagID);
3833 }

3835 static StringRef mangleAArch64VectorBase(const BuiltinType *EltType) {
3836  switch (EltType->getKind()) {
3837  case BuiltinType::SChar:
3838  return "Int8";
3839  case BuiltinType::Short:
3840  return "Int16";
3841  case BuiltinType::Int:
3842  return "Int32";
3843  case BuiltinType::Long:
3844  case BuiltinType::LongLong:
3845  return "Int64";
3846  case BuiltinType::UChar:
3847  return "Uint8";
3848  case BuiltinType::UShort:
3849  return "Uint16";
3850  case BuiltinType::UInt:
3851  return "Uint32";
3852  case BuiltinType::ULong:
3853  case BuiltinType::ULongLong:
3854  return "Uint64";
3855  case BuiltinType::Half:
3856  return "Float16";
3857  case BuiltinType::Float:
3858  return "Float32";
3859  case BuiltinType::Double:
3860  return "Float64";
3861  case BuiltinType::BFloat16:
3862  return "Bfloat16";
3863  default:
3864  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected vector element base type");
3865  }
3866 }

3868 // AArch64's ABI for Neon vector types specifies that they should be mangled as
3869 // the equivalent internal name. The vector type must be one of the special
3870 // types predefined by ARM.
3871 void CXXNameMangler::mangleAArch64NeonVectorType(const VectorType *T) {
3872  QualType EltType = T->getElementType();
3873  assert(EltType->isBuiltinType() && "Neon vector element not a BuiltinType");
3874  unsigned BitSize =
3875  (T->getNumElements() * getASTContext().getTypeSize(EltType));
3876  (void)BitSize; // Silence warning.
3877 
3878  assert((BitSize == 64 || BitSize == 128) &&
3879  "Neon vector type not 64 or 128 bits");
3880 
3881  StringRef EltName;
3882  if (T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::NeonPoly) {
3883  switch (cast<BuiltinType>(EltType)->getKind()) {
3884  case BuiltinType::UChar:
3885  EltName = "Poly8";
3886  break;
3887  case BuiltinType::UShort:
3888  EltName = "Poly16";
3889  break;
3890  case BuiltinType::ULong:
3891  case BuiltinType::ULongLong:
3892  EltName = "Poly64";
3893  break;
3894  default:
3895  llvm_unreachable("unexpected Neon polynomial vector element type");
3896  }
3897  } else
3898  EltName = mangleAArch64VectorBase(cast<BuiltinType>(EltType));
3899 
3900  std::string TypeName =
3901  ("__" + EltName + "x" + Twine(T->getNumElements()) + "_t").str();
3902  Out << TypeName.length() << TypeName;
3903 }
3904 void CXXNameMangler::mangleAArch64NeonVectorType(const DependentVectorType *T) {
3905  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags = Context.getDiags();
3906  unsigned DiagID = Diags.getCustomDiagID(
3907  DiagnosticsEngine::Error,
3908  "cannot mangle this dependent neon vector type yet");
3909  Diags.Report(T->getAttributeLoc(), DiagID);
3910 }
3911 
3912 // The AArch64 ACLE specifies that fixed-length SVE vector and predicate types
3913 // defined with the 'arm_sve_vector_bits' attribute map to the same AAPCS64
3914 // type as the sizeless variants.
3915 //
3916 // The mangling scheme for VLS types is implemented as a "pseudo" template:
3917 //
3918 // '__SVE_VLS<<type>, <vector length>>'
3919 //
3920 // Combining the existing SVE type and a specific vector length (in bits).
3921 // For example:
3922 //
3923 // typedef __SVInt32_t foo __attribute__((arm_sve_vector_bits(512)));
3924 //
3925 // is described as '__SVE_VLS<__SVInt32_t, 512u>' and mangled as:
3926 //
3927 // "9__SVE_VLSI" + base type mangling + "Lj" + __ARM_FEATURE_SVE_BITS + "EE"
3928 //
3929 // i.e. 9__SVE_VLSIu11__SVInt32_tLj512EE
3930 //
3931 // The latest ACLE specification (00bet5) does not contain details of this
3932 // mangling scheme, it will be specified in the next revision. The mangling
3933 // scheme is otherwise defined in the appendices to the Procedure Call Standard
3934 // for the Arm Architecture, see
3935 // https://github.com/ARM-software/abi-aa/blob/main/aapcs64/aapcs64.rst#appendix-c-mangling
3936 void CXXNameMangler::mangleAArch64FixedSveVectorType(const VectorType *T) {
3937  assert((T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::SveFixedLengthData ||
3938  T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::SveFixedLengthPredicate) &&
3939  "expected fixed-length SVE vector!");
3940 
3941  QualType EltType = T->getElementType();
3942  assert(EltType->isBuiltinType() &&
3943  "expected builtin type for fixed-length SVE vector!");
3944 
3945  StringRef TypeName;
3946  switch (cast<BuiltinType>(EltType)->getKind()) {
3947  case BuiltinType::SChar:
3948  TypeName = "__SVInt8_t";
3949  break;
3950  case BuiltinType::UChar: {
3951  if (T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::SveFixedLengthData)
3952  TypeName = "__SVUint8_t";
3953  else
3954  TypeName = "__SVBool_t";
3955  break;
3956  }
3957  case BuiltinType::Short:
3958  TypeName = "__SVInt16_t";
3959  break;
3960  case BuiltinType::UShort:
3961  TypeName = "__SVUint16_t";
3962  break;
3963  case BuiltinType::Int:
3964  TypeName = "__SVInt32_t";
3965  break;
3966  case BuiltinType::UInt:
3967  TypeName = "__SVUint32_t";
3968  break;
3969  case BuiltinType::Long:
3970  TypeName = "__SVInt64_t";
3971  break;
3972  case BuiltinType::ULong:
3973  TypeName = "__SVUint64_t";
3974  break;
3975  case BuiltinType::Half:
3976  TypeName = "__SVFloat16_t";
3977  break;
3978  case BuiltinType::Float:
3979  TypeName = "__SVFloat32_t";
3980  break;
3981  case BuiltinType::Double:
3982  TypeName = "__SVFloat64_t";
3983  break;
3984  case BuiltinType::BFloat16:
3985  TypeName = "__SVBfloat16_t";
3986  break;
3987  default:
3988  llvm_unreachable("unexpected element type for fixed-length SVE vector!");
3989  }
3990 
3991  unsigned VecSizeInBits = getASTContext().getTypeInfo(T).Width;
3992 
3993  if (T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::SveFixedLengthPredicate)
3994  VecSizeInBits *= 8;
3995 
3996  Out << "9__SVE_VLSI" << 'u' << TypeName.size() << TypeName << "Lj"
3997  << VecSizeInBits << "EE";
3998 }

4000 void CXXNameMangler::mangleAArch64FixedSveVectorType(
4001  const DependentVectorType *T) {
4002  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags = Context.getDiags();

4004  DiagnosticsEngine::Error,

4009 void CXXNameMangler::mangleRISCVFixedRVVVectorType(const VectorType *T) {
4010  assert((T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::RVVFixedLengthData ||
4011  T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::RVVFixedLengthMask) &&
4012  "expected fixed-length RVV vector!");
4013 
4014  QualType EltType = T->getElementType();
4015  assert(EltType->isBuiltinType() &&
4016  "expected builtin type for fixed-length RVV vector!");
4017 
4018  SmallString<20> TypeNameStr;
4019  llvm::raw_svector_ostream TypeNameOS(TypeNameStr);
4020  TypeNameOS << "__rvv_";
4021  switch (cast<BuiltinType>(EltType)->getKind()) {
4022  case BuiltinType::SChar:
4023  TypeNameOS << "int8";
4024  break;
4025  case BuiltinType::UChar:
4026  if (T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::RVVFixedLengthData)
4027  TypeNameOS << "uint8";
4028  else
4029  TypeNameOS << "bool";
4030  break;
4031  case BuiltinType::Short:
4032  TypeNameOS << "int16";
4033  break;
4034  case BuiltinType::UShort:
4035  TypeNameOS << "uint16";
4036  break;
4037  case BuiltinType::Int:
4038  TypeNameOS << "int32";
4039  break;
4040  case BuiltinType::UInt:
4041  TypeNameOS << "uint32";
4042  break;
4043  case BuiltinType::Long:
4044  TypeNameOS << "int64";
4045  break;
4046  case BuiltinType::ULong:
4047  TypeNameOS << "uint64";
4048  break;
4049  case BuiltinType::Float16:
4050  TypeNameOS << "float16";
4051  break;
4052  case BuiltinType::Float:
4053  TypeNameOS << "float32";
4054  break;
4055  case BuiltinType::Double:
4056  TypeNameOS << "float64";
4057  break;
4058  default:
4059  llvm_unreachable("unexpected element type for fixed-length RVV vector!");
4060  }
4061 
4062  unsigned VecSizeInBits = getASTContext().getTypeInfo(T).Width;
4063 
4064  // Apend the LMUL suffix.
4065  auto VScale = getASTContext().getTargetInfo().getVScaleRange(
4066  getASTContext().getLangOpts());
4067  unsigned VLen = VScale->first * llvm::RISCV::RVVBitsPerBlock;
4068 
4069  if (T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::RVVFixedLengthData) {
4070  TypeNameOS << 'm';
4071  if (VecSizeInBits >= VLen)
4072  TypeNameOS << (VecSizeInBits / VLen);
4073  else
4074  TypeNameOS << 'f' << (VLen / VecSizeInBits);
4075  } else {
4076  TypeNameOS << (VLen / VecSizeInBits);
4077  }
4078  TypeNameOS << "_t";
4079 
4080  Out << "9__RVV_VLSI" << 'u' << TypeNameStr.size() << TypeNameStr << "Lj"
4081  << VecSizeInBits << "EE";
4082 }

4084 void CXXNameMangler::mangleRISCVFixedRVVVectorType(
4085  const DependentVectorType *T) {
4086  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags = Context.getDiags();
4087  unsigned DiagID = Diags.getCustomDiagID(
4088  DiagnosticsEngine::Error,
4089  "cannot mangle this dependent fixed-length RVV vector type yet");
4090  Diags.Report(T->getAttributeLoc(), DiagID);
4091 }
4092 
4093 // GNU extension: vector types
4094 // <type> ::= <vector-type>
4095 // <vector-type> ::= Dv <positive dimension number> _
4096 // <extended element type>
4097 // ::= Dv [<dimension expression>] _ <element type>
4098 // <extended element type> ::= <element type>
4099 // ::= p # AltiVec vector pixel
4100 // ::= b # Altivec vector bool
4101 void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const VectorType *T) {
4102  if ((T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::Neon ||
4103  T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::NeonPoly)) {
4104  llvm::Triple Target = getASTContext().getTargetInfo().getTriple();
4105  llvm::Triple::ArchType Arch =
4106  getASTContext().getTargetInfo().getTriple().getArch();
4107  if ((Arch == llvm::Triple::aarch64 ||
4108  Arch == llvm::Triple::aarch64_be) && !Target.isOSDarwin())
4109  mangleAArch64NeonVectorType(T);
4110  else
4111  mangleNeonVectorType(T);
4112  return;
4113  } else if (T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::SveFixedLengthData ||
4114  T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::SveFixedLengthPredicate) {
4115  mangleAArch64FixedSveVectorType(T);
4116  return;
4117  } else if (T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::RVVFixedLengthData ||
4118  T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::RVVFixedLengthMask) {
4119  mangleRISCVFixedRVVVectorType(T);
4120  return;
4121  }
4122  Out << "Dv" << T->getNumElements() << '_';
4123  if (T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::AltiVecPixel)
4124  Out << 'p';
4125  else if (T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::AltiVecBool)
4126  Out << 'b';
4127  else
4128  mangleType(T->getElementType());
4129 }
4130 
4131 void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const DependentVectorType *T) {
4132  if ((T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::Neon ||
4133  T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::NeonPoly)) {
4134  llvm::Triple Target = getASTContext().getTargetInfo().getTriple();
4135  llvm::Triple::ArchType Arch =
4136  getASTContext().getTargetInfo().getTriple().getArch();
4137  if ((Arch == llvm::Triple::aarch64 || Arch == llvm::Triple::aarch64_be) &&
4138  !Target.isOSDarwin())
4139  mangleAArch64NeonVectorType(T);
4140  else
4141  mangleNeonVectorType(T);
4142  return;
4143  } else if (T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::SveFixedLengthData ||
4144  T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::SveFixedLengthPredicate) {
4145  mangleAArch64FixedSveVectorType(T);
4146  return;
4147  } else if (T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::RVVFixedLengthData) {
4148  mangleRISCVFixedRVVVectorType(T);
4149  return;
4150  }
4151 
4152  Out << "Dv";
4153  mangleExpression(T->getSizeExpr());
4154  Out << '_';
4155  if (T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::AltiVecPixel)
4156  Out << 'p';
4157  else if (T->getVectorKind() == VectorKind::AltiVecBool)
4158  Out << 'b';
4159  else
4160  mangleType(T->getElementType());
4161 }

4163 void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const ExtVectorType *T) {
4164  mangleType(static_cast<const VectorType*>(T));
4165 }
4166 void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const DependentSizedExtVectorType *T) {
4167  Out << "Dv";
4168  mangleExpression(T->getSizeExpr());
4169  Out << '_';
4170  mangleType(T->getElementType());
4171 }
4172 
4173 void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const ConstantMatrixType *T) {
4174  // Mangle matrix types as a vendor extended type:
4175  // u<Len>matrix_typeI<Rows><Columns><element type>E
4176 
4177  StringRef VendorQualifier = "matrix_type";
4178  Out << "u" << VendorQualifier.size() << VendorQualifier;
4179 
4180  Out << "I";
4181  auto &ASTCtx = getASTContext();
4182  unsigned BitWidth = ASTCtx.getTypeSize(ASTCtx.getSizeType());
4183  llvm::APSInt Rows(BitWidth);
4184  Rows = T->getNumRows();
4185  mangleIntegerLiteral(ASTCtx.getSizeType(), Rows);
4186  llvm::APSInt Columns(BitWidth);
4187  Columns = T->getNumColumns();
4188  mangleIntegerLiteral(ASTCtx.getSizeType(), Columns);
4189  mangleType(T->getElementType());
4190  Out << "E";
4191 }

4194  // Mangle matrix types as a vendor extended type:
4195  // u<Len>matrix_typeI<row expr><column expr><element type>E
4196  StringRef VendorQualifier = "matrix_type";
4197  Out << "u" << VendorQualifier.size() << VendorQualifier;
4198 
4199  Out << "I";
4200  mangleTemplateArgExpr(T->getRowExpr());
4201  mangleTemplateArgExpr(T->getColumnExpr());
4202  mangleType(T->getElementType());
4203  Out << "E";
4204 }

4229 void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const ObjCObjectType *T) {
4230  // Treat __kindof as a vendor extended type qualifier.
4231  if (T->isKindOfType())
4232  Out << "U8__kindof";
4233 
4234  if (!T->qual_empty()) {
4235  // Mangle protocol qualifiers.
4236  SmallString<64> QualStr;
4237  llvm::raw_svector_ostream QualOS(QualStr);
4238  QualOS << "objcproto";
4239  for (const auto *I : T->quals()) {
4240  StringRef name = I->getName();
4241  QualOS << name.size() << name;
4242  }
4243  Out << 'U' << QualStr.size() << QualStr;
4244  }
4245 
4246  mangleType(T->getBaseType());
4247 
4248  if (T->isSpecialized()) {
4249  // Mangle type arguments as I <type>+ E
4250  Out << 'I';
4251  for (auto typeArg : T->getTypeArgs())
4252  mangleType(typeArg);
4253  Out << 'E';
4254  }
4255 }

4258  Out << "U13block_pointer";
4259  mangleType(T->getPointeeType());
4260 }

4263  // Mangle injected class name types as if the user had written the
4264  // specialization out fully. It may not actually be possible to see
4265  // this mangling, though.

4269 void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const TemplateSpecializationType *T) {
4270  if (TemplateDecl *TD = T->getTemplateName().getAsTemplateDecl()) {
4271  mangleTemplateName(TD, T->template_arguments());
4272  } else {
4273  if (mangleSubstitution(QualType(T, 0)))
4274  return;
4275 
4276  mangleTemplatePrefix(T->getTemplateName());
4277 
4278  // FIXME: GCC does not appear to mangle the template arguments when
4279  // the template in question is a dependent template name. Should we
4280  // emulate that badness?
4281  mangleTemplateArgs(T->getTemplateName(), T->template_arguments());
4282  addSubstitution(QualType(T, 0));
4283  }
4284 }
4285 
4286 void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const DependentNameType *T) {
4287  // Proposal by cxx-abi-dev, 2014-03-26
4288  // <class-enum-type> ::= <name> # non-dependent or dependent type name or
4289  // # dependent elaborated type specifier using
4290  // # 'typename'
4291  // ::= Ts <name> # dependent elaborated type specifier using
4292  // # 'struct' or 'class'
4293  // ::= Tu <name> # dependent elaborated type specifier using
4294  // # 'union'
4295  // ::= Te <name> # dependent elaborated type specifier using
4296  // # 'enum'
4297  switch (T->getKeyword()) {
4298  case ElaboratedTypeKeyword::None:
4299  case ElaboratedTypeKeyword::Typename:
4300  break;
4301  case ElaboratedTypeKeyword::Struct:
4302  case ElaboratedTypeKeyword::Class:
4303  case ElaboratedTypeKeyword::Interface:
4304  Out << "Ts";
4305  break;
4306  case ElaboratedTypeKeyword::Union:
4307  Out << "Tu";
4308  break;
4309  case ElaboratedTypeKeyword::Enum:
4310  Out << "Te";
4311  break;
4312  }
4313  // Typename types are always nested
4314  Out << 'N';
4315  manglePrefix(T->getQualifier());
4316  mangleSourceName(T->getIdentifier());
4317  Out << 'E';
4318 }
4319 
4320 void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const DependentTemplateSpecializationType *T) {
4321  // Dependently-scoped template types are nested if they have a prefix.
4322  Out << 'N';
4323 
4324  // TODO: avoid making this TemplateName.
4325  TemplateName Prefix =
4326  getASTContext().getDependentTemplateName(T->getQualifier(),
4327  T->getIdentifier());
4328  mangleTemplatePrefix(Prefix);
4329 
4330  // FIXME: GCC does not appear to mangle the template arguments when
4331  // the template in question is a dependent template name. Should we
4332  // emulate that badness?
4333  mangleTemplateArgs(Prefix, T->template_arguments());
4334  Out << 'E';
4335 }

4339  // "extension with parameters" mangling.

4343 void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const TypeOfExprType *T) {
4344  // FIXME: this is pretty unsatisfactory, but there isn't an obvious
4345  // "extension with parameters" mangling.

4348 
4349 void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const DecltypeType *T) {
4350  Expr *E = T->getUnderlyingExpr();
4351 
4352  // type ::= Dt <expression> E # decltype of an id-expression
4353  // # or class member access
4354  // ::= DT <expression> E # decltype of an expression
4355 
4356  // This purports to be an exhaustive list of id-expressions and
4357  // class member accesses. Note that we do not ignore parentheses;
4358  // parentheses change the semantics of decltype for these
4359  // expressions (and cause the mangler to use the other form).
4360  if (isa<DeclRefExpr>(E) ||
4361  isa<MemberExpr>(E) ||
4362  isa<UnresolvedLookupExpr>(E) ||
4363  isa<DependentScopeDeclRefExpr>(E) ||
4364  isa<CXXDependentScopeMemberExpr>(E) ||
4365  isa<UnresolvedMemberExpr>(E))
4366  Out << "Dt";
4367  else
4368  Out << "DT";
4369  mangleExpression(E);
4370  Out << 'E';
4371 }
4372 
4373 void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const UnaryTransformType *T) {
4374  // If this is dependent, we need to record that. If not, we simply
4375  // mangle it as the underlying type since they are equivalent.
4376  if (T->isDependentType()) {
4377  Out << "u";
4378 
4379  StringRef BuiltinName;
4380  switch (T->getUTTKind()) {
4381 #define TRANSFORM_TYPE_TRAIT_DEF(Enum, Trait) \
4382  case UnaryTransformType::Enum: \
4383  BuiltinName = "__" #Trait; \
4384  break;
4385 #include "clang/Basic/TransformTypeTraits.def"
4386  }
4387  Out << BuiltinName.size() << BuiltinName;
4388  }
4389 
4390  Out << "I";
4391  mangleType(T->getBaseType());
4392  Out << "E";
4393 }
4394 
4395 void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const AutoType *T) {
4396  assert(T->getDeducedType().isNull() &&
4397  "Deduced AutoType shouldn't be handled here!");
4398  assert(T->getKeyword() != AutoTypeKeyword::GNUAutoType &&
4399  "shouldn't need to mangle __auto_type!");
4400  // <builtin-type> ::= Da # auto
4401  // ::= Dc # decltype(auto)
4402  // ::= Dk # constrained auto
4403  // ::= DK # constrained decltype(auto)
4404  if (T->isConstrained() && !isCompatibleWith(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver17)) {
4405  Out << (T->isDecltypeAuto() ? "DK" : "Dk");
4406  mangleTypeConstraint(T->getTypeConstraintConcept(),
4407  T->getTypeConstraintArguments());
4408  } else {
4409  Out << (T->isDecltypeAuto() ? "Dc" : "Da");
4410  }
4411 }
4412 
4413 void CXXNameMangler::mangleType(const DeducedTemplateSpecializationType *T) {
4414  QualType Deduced = T->getDeducedType();
4415  if (!Deduced.isNull())
4416  return mangleType(Deduced);
4417 
4418  TemplateDecl *TD = T->getTemplateName().getAsTemplateDecl();
4419  assert(TD && "shouldn't form deduced TST unless we know we have a template");
4420 
4421  if (mangleSubstitution(TD))
4422  return;
4423 
4424  mangleName(GlobalDecl(TD));
4425  addSubstitution(TD);
4426 }

4462 void CXXNameMangler::mangleIntegerLiteral(QualType T,
4463  const llvm::APSInt &Value) {
4464  // <expr-primary> ::= L <type> <value number> E # integer literal
4465  Out << 'L';
4466 
4467  mangleType(T);
4468  if (T->isBooleanType()) {
4469  // Boolean values are encoded as 0/1.
4470  Out << (Value.getBoolValue() ? '1' : '0');
4471  } else {
4472  mangleNumber(Value);
4473  }
4474  Out << 'E';
4475 
4476 }
4477 
4478 void CXXNameMangler::mangleMemberExprBase(const Expr *Base, bool IsArrow) {
4479  // Ignore member expressions involving anonymous unions.
4480  while (const auto *RT = Base->getType()->getAs<RecordType>()) {
4481  if (!RT->getDecl()->isAnonymousStructOrUnion())
4482  break;
4483  const auto *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(Base);
4484  if (!ME)
4485  break;
4486  Base = ME->getBase();
4487  IsArrow = ME->isArrow();
4488  }
4489 
4490  if (Base->isImplicitCXXThis()) {
4491  // Note: GCC mangles member expressions to the implicit 'this' as
4492  // *this., whereas we represent them as this->. The Itanium C++ ABI
4493  // does not specify anything here, so we follow GCC.
4494  Out << "dtdefpT";
4495  } else {
4496  Out << (IsArrow ? "pt" : "dt");
4497  mangleExpression(Base);
4498  }
4499 }
4500 
4501 /// Mangles a member expression.
4502 void CXXNameMangler::mangleMemberExpr(const Expr *base,
4503  bool isArrow,
4504  NestedNameSpecifier *qualifier,
4505  NamedDecl *firstQualifierLookup,
4506  DeclarationName member,
4507  const TemplateArgumentLoc *TemplateArgs,
4508  unsigned NumTemplateArgs,
4509  unsigned arity) {
4510  // <expression> ::= dt <expression> <unresolved-name>
4511  // ::= pt <expression> <unresolved-name>
4512  if (base)
4513  mangleMemberExprBase(base, isArrow);
4514  mangleUnresolvedName(qualifier, member, TemplateArgs, NumTemplateArgs, arity);
4515 }
4516 
4517 /// Look at the callee of the given call expression and determine if
4518 /// it's a parenthesized id-expression which would have triggered ADL
4519 /// otherwise.
4520 static bool isParenthesizedADLCallee(const CallExpr *call) {
4521  const Expr *callee = call->getCallee();
4522  const Expr *fn = callee->IgnoreParens();
4523 
4524  // Must be parenthesized. IgnoreParens() skips __extension__ nodes,
4525  // too, but for those to appear in the callee, it would have to be
4526  // parenthesized.
4527  if (callee == fn) return false;
4528 
4529  // Must be an unresolved lookup.
4530  const UnresolvedLookupExpr *lookup = dyn_cast<UnresolvedLookupExpr>(fn);
4531  if (!lookup) return false;
4532 
4533  assert(!lookup->requiresADL());
4534 
4535  // Must be an unqualified lookup.
4536  if (lookup->getQualifier()) return false;
4537 
4538  // Must not have found a class member. Note that if one is a class
4539  // member, they're all class members.
4540  if (lookup->getNumDecls() > 0 &&
4541  (*lookup->decls_begin())->isCXXClassMember())
4542  return false;
4543 
4544  // Otherwise, ADL would have been triggered.
4545  return true;
4546 }
4547 
4548 void CXXNameMangler::mangleCastExpression(const Expr *E, StringRef CastEncoding) {
4549  const ExplicitCastExpr *ECE = cast<ExplicitCastExpr>(E);
4550  Out << CastEncoding;
4551  mangleType(ECE->getType());
4552  mangleExpression(ECE->getSubExpr());
4553 }
