4555 void CXXNameMangler::mangleInitListElements(const InitListExpr *InitList) {
4556  if (auto *Syntactic = InitList->getSyntacticForm())
4557  InitList = Syntactic;
4558  for (unsigned i = 0, e = InitList->getNumInits(); i != e; ++i)
4559  mangleExpression(InitList->getInit(i));
4560 }
4561 
4562 void CXXNameMangler::mangleRequirement(SourceLocation RequiresExprLoc,
4563  const concepts::Requirement *Req) {
4564  using concepts::Requirement;
4565 
4566  // TODO: We can't mangle the result of a failed substitution. It's not clear
4567  // whether we should be mangling the original form prior to any substitution
4568  // instead. See https://lists.isocpp.org/core/2023/04/14118.php
4569  auto HandleSubstitutionFailure =
4570  [&](SourceLocation Loc) {
4571  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags = Context.getDiags();
4572  unsigned DiagID = Diags.getCustomDiagID(
4573  DiagnosticsEngine::Error, "cannot mangle this requires-expression "
4574  "containing a substitution failure");
4575  Diags.Report(Loc, DiagID);
4576  Out << 'F';
4577  };
4578 
4579  switch (Req->getKind()) {
4580  case Requirement::RK_Type: {
4581  const auto *TR = cast<concepts::TypeRequirement>(Req);
4582  if (TR->isSubstitutionFailure())
4583  return HandleSubstitutionFailure(
4584  TR->getSubstitutionDiagnostic()->DiagLoc);
4585 
4586  Out << 'T';
4587  mangleType(TR->getType()->getType());
4588  break;
4589  }
4590 
4591  case Requirement::RK_Simple:
4592  case Requirement::RK_Compound: {
4593  const auto *ER = cast<concepts::ExprRequirement>(Req);
4594  if (ER->isExprSubstitutionFailure())
4595  return HandleSubstitutionFailure(
4596  ER->getExprSubstitutionDiagnostic()->DiagLoc);
4597 
4598  Out << 'X';
4599  mangleExpression(ER->getExpr());
4600 
4601  if (ER->hasNoexceptRequirement())
4602  Out << 'N';
4603 
4604  if (!ER->getReturnTypeRequirement().isEmpty()) {
4605  if (ER->getReturnTypeRequirement().isSubstitutionFailure())
4606  return HandleSubstitutionFailure(ER->getReturnTypeRequirement()
4607  .getSubstitutionDiagnostic()
4608  ->DiagLoc);
4609 
4610  Out << 'R';
4611  mangleTypeConstraint(ER->getReturnTypeRequirement().getTypeConstraint());
4612  }
4613  break;
4614  }
4615 
4616  case Requirement::RK_Nested:
4617  const auto *NR = cast<concepts::NestedRequirement>(Req);
4618  if (NR->hasInvalidConstraint()) {
4619  // FIXME: NestedRequirement should track the location of its requires
4620  // keyword.
4621  return HandleSubstitutionFailure(RequiresExprLoc);
4622  }
4623 
4624  Out << 'Q';
4625  mangleExpression(NR->getConstraintExpr());
4626  break;
4627  }
4628 }
4629 
4630 void CXXNameMangler::mangleExpression(const Expr *E, unsigned Arity,
4631  bool AsTemplateArg) {
4632  // <expression> ::= <unary operator-name> <expression>
4633  // ::= <binary operator-name> <expression> <expression>
4634  // ::= <trinary operator-name> <expression> <expression> <expression>
4635  // ::= cv <type> expression # conversion with one argument
4636  // ::= cv <type> _ <expression>* E # conversion with a different number of arguments
4637  // ::= dc <type> <expression> # dynamic_cast<type> (expression)
4638  // ::= sc <type> <expression> # static_cast<type> (expression)
4639  // ::= cc <type> <expression> # const_cast<type> (expression)
4640  // ::= rc <type> <expression> # reinterpret_cast<type> (expression)
4641  // ::= st <type> # sizeof (a type)
4642  // ::= at <type> # alignof (a type)
4643  // ::= <template-param>
4644  // ::= <function-param>
4645  // ::= fpT # 'this' expression (part of <function-param>)
4646  // ::= sr <type> <unqualified-name> # dependent name
4647  // ::= sr <type> <unqualified-name> <template-args> # dependent template-id
4648  // ::= ds <expression> <expression> # expr.*expr
4649  // ::= sZ <template-param> # size of a parameter pack
4650  // ::= sZ <function-param> # size of a function parameter pack
4651  // ::= u <source-name> <template-arg>* E # vendor extended expression
4652  // ::= <expr-primary>
4653  // <expr-primary> ::= L <type> <value number> E # integer literal
4654  // ::= L <type> <value float> E # floating literal
4655  // ::= L <type> <string type> E # string literal
4656  // ::= L <nullptr type> E # nullptr literal "LDnE"
4657  // ::= L <pointer type> 0 E # null pointer template argument
4658  // ::= L <type> <real-part float> _ <imag-part float> E # complex floating point literal (C99); not used by clang
4659  // ::= L <mangled-name> E # external name
4660  QualType ImplicitlyConvertedToType;
4661 
4662  // A top-level expression that's not <expr-primary> needs to be wrapped in
4663  // X...E in a template arg.
4664  bool IsPrimaryExpr = true;
4665  auto NotPrimaryExpr = [&] {
4666  if (AsTemplateArg && IsPrimaryExpr)
4667  Out << 'X';
4668  IsPrimaryExpr = false;
4669  };
4670 
4671  auto MangleDeclRefExpr = [&](const NamedDecl *D) {
4672  switch (D->getKind()) {
4673  default:
4674  // <expr-primary> ::= L <mangled-name> E # external name
4675  Out << 'L';
4676  mangle(D);
4677  Out << 'E';
4678  break;
4679 
4680  case Decl::ParmVar:
4681  NotPrimaryExpr();
4682  mangleFunctionParam(cast<ParmVarDecl>(D));
4683  break;
4684 
4685  case Decl::EnumConstant: {
4686  // <expr-primary>
4687  const EnumConstantDecl *ED = cast<EnumConstantDecl>(D);
4688  mangleIntegerLiteral(ED->getType(), ED->getInitVal());
4689  break;
4690  }
4691 
4692  case Decl::NonTypeTemplateParm:
4693  NotPrimaryExpr();
4694  const NonTypeTemplateParmDecl *PD = cast<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(D);
4695  mangleTemplateParameter(PD->getDepth(), PD->getIndex());
4696  break;
4697  }
4698  };
4699 
4700  // 'goto recurse' is used when handling a simple "unwrapping" node which
4701  // produces no output, where ImplicitlyConvertedToType and AsTemplateArg need
4702  // to be preserved.
4703 recurse:
4704  switch (E->getStmtClass()) {
4705  case Expr::NoStmtClass:
4706 #define ABSTRACT_STMT(Type)
4707 #define EXPR(Type, Base)
4708 #define STMT(Type, Base) \
4709  case Expr::Type##Class:
4710 #include "clang/AST/StmtNodes.inc"
4711  // fallthrough
4712 
4713  // These all can only appear in local or variable-initialization
4714  // contexts and so should never appear in a mangling.
4715  case Expr::AddrLabelExprClass:
4716  case Expr::DesignatedInitUpdateExprClass:
4717  case Expr::ImplicitValueInitExprClass:
4718  case Expr::ArrayInitLoopExprClass:
4719  case Expr::ArrayInitIndexExprClass:
4720  case Expr::NoInitExprClass:
4721  case Expr::ParenListExprClass:
4722  case Expr::MSPropertyRefExprClass:
4723  case Expr::MSPropertySubscriptExprClass:
4724  case Expr::TypoExprClass: // This should no longer exist in the AST by now.
4725  case Expr::RecoveryExprClass:
4726  case Expr::OMPArraySectionExprClass:
4727  case Expr::OMPArrayShapingExprClass:
4728  case Expr::OMPIteratorExprClass:
4729  case Expr::CXXInheritedCtorInitExprClass:
4730  case Expr::CXXParenListInitExprClass:
4731  case Expr::PackIndexingExprClass:
4732  llvm_unreachable("unexpected statement kind");
4733 
4734  case Expr::ConstantExprClass:
4735  E = cast<ConstantExpr>(E)->getSubExpr();
4736  goto recurse;
4737 
4738  // FIXME: invent manglings for all these.
4739  case Expr::BlockExprClass:
4740  case Expr::ChooseExprClass:
4741  case Expr::CompoundLiteralExprClass:
4742  case Expr::ExtVectorElementExprClass:
4743  case Expr::GenericSelectionExprClass:
4744  case Expr::ObjCEncodeExprClass:
4745  case Expr::ObjCIsaExprClass:
4746  case Expr::ObjCIvarRefExprClass:
4747  case Expr::ObjCMessageExprClass:
4748  case Expr::ObjCPropertyRefExprClass:
4749  case Expr::ObjCProtocolExprClass:
4750  case Expr::ObjCSelectorExprClass:
4751  case Expr::ObjCStringLiteralClass:
4752  case Expr::ObjCBoxedExprClass:
4753  case Expr::ObjCArrayLiteralClass:
4754  case Expr::ObjCDictionaryLiteralClass:
4755  case Expr::ObjCSubscriptRefExprClass:
4756  case Expr::ObjCIndirectCopyRestoreExprClass:
4757  case Expr::ObjCAvailabilityCheckExprClass:
4758  case Expr::OffsetOfExprClass:
4759  case Expr::PredefinedExprClass:
4760  case Expr::ShuffleVectorExprClass:
4761  case Expr::ConvertVectorExprClass:
4762  case Expr::StmtExprClass:
4763  case Expr::ArrayTypeTraitExprClass:
4764  case Expr::ExpressionTraitExprClass:
4765  case Expr::VAArgExprClass:
4766  case Expr::CUDAKernelCallExprClass:
4767  case Expr::AsTypeExprClass:
4768  case Expr::PseudoObjectExprClass:
4769  case Expr::AtomicExprClass:
4770  case Expr::SourceLocExprClass:
4771  case Expr::BuiltinBitCastExprClass:
4772  case Expr::SYCLBuiltinNumFieldsExprClass:
4773  case Expr::SYCLBuiltinFieldTypeExprClass:
4774  case Expr::SYCLBuiltinNumBasesExprClass:
4775  case Expr::SYCLBuiltinBaseTypeExprClass:
4776  {
4777  NotPrimaryExpr();
4778  if (!NullOut) {
4779  // As bad as this diagnostic is, it's better than crashing.
4780  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags = Context.getDiags();
4781  unsigned DiagID = Diags.getCustomDiagID(DiagnosticsEngine::Error,
4782  "cannot yet mangle expression type %0");
4783  Diags.Report(E->getExprLoc(), DiagID)
4784  << E->getStmtClassName() << E->getSourceRange();
4785  return;
4786  }
4787  break;
4788  }
4789 
4790  case Expr::CXXUuidofExprClass: {
4791  NotPrimaryExpr();
4792  const CXXUuidofExpr *UE = cast<CXXUuidofExpr>(E);
4793  // As of clang 12, uuidof uses the vendor extended expression
4794  // mangling. Previously, it used a special-cased nonstandard extension.
4795  if (!isCompatibleWith(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver11)) {
4796  Out << "u8__uuidof";
4797  if (UE->isTypeOperand())
4798  mangleType(UE->getTypeOperand(Context.getASTContext()));
4799  else
4800  mangleTemplateArgExpr(UE->getExprOperand());
4801  Out << 'E';
4802  } else {
4803  if (UE->isTypeOperand()) {
4804  QualType UuidT = UE->getTypeOperand(Context.getASTContext());
4805  Out << "u8__uuidoft";
4806  mangleType(UuidT);
4807  } else {
4808  Expr *UuidExp = UE->getExprOperand();
4809  Out << "u8__uuidofz";
4810  mangleExpression(UuidExp);
4811  }
4812  }
4813  break;
4814  }
4815 
4816  // Even gcc-4.5 doesn't mangle this.
4817  case Expr::BinaryConditionalOperatorClass: {
4818  NotPrimaryExpr();
4819  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags = Context.getDiags();
4820  unsigned DiagID =
4821  Diags.getCustomDiagID(DiagnosticsEngine::Error,
4822  "?: operator with omitted middle operand cannot be mangled");
4823  Diags.Report(E->getExprLoc(), DiagID)
4824  << E->getStmtClassName() << E->getSourceRange();
4825  return;
4826  }
4827 
4828  // These are used for internal purposes and cannot be meaningfully mangled.
4829  case Expr::OpaqueValueExprClass:
4830  llvm_unreachable("cannot mangle opaque value; mangling wrong thing?");
4831 
4832  case Expr::InitListExprClass: {
4833  NotPrimaryExpr();
4834  Out << "il";
4835  mangleInitListElements(cast<InitListExpr>(E));
4836  Out << "E";
4837  break;
4838  }
4839 
4840  case Expr::DesignatedInitExprClass: {
4841  NotPrimaryExpr();
4842  auto *DIE = cast<DesignatedInitExpr>(E);
4843  for (const auto &Designator : DIE->designators()) {
4844  if (Designator.isFieldDesignator()) {
4845  Out << "di";
4846  mangleSourceName(Designator.getFieldName());
4847  } else if (Designator.isArrayDesignator()) {
4848  Out << "dx";
4849  mangleExpression(DIE->getArrayIndex(Designator));
4850  } else {
4851  assert(Designator.isArrayRangeDesignator() &&
4852  "unknown designator kind");
4853  Out << "dX";
4854  mangleExpression(DIE->getArrayRangeStart(Designator));
4855  mangleExpression(DIE->getArrayRangeEnd(Designator));
4856  }
4857  }
4858  mangleExpression(DIE->getInit());
4859  break;
4860  }
4861 
4862  case Expr::CXXDefaultArgExprClass:
4863  E = cast<CXXDefaultArgExpr>(E)->getExpr();
4864  goto recurse;
4865 
4866  case Expr::CXXDefaultInitExprClass:
4867  E = cast<CXXDefaultInitExpr>(E)->getExpr();
4868  goto recurse;
4869 
4870  case Expr::CXXStdInitializerListExprClass:
4871  E = cast<CXXStdInitializerListExpr>(E)->getSubExpr();
4872  goto recurse;
4873 
4874  case Expr::SubstNonTypeTemplateParmExprClass: {
4875  // Mangle a substituted parameter the same way we mangle the template
4876  // argument.
4877  auto *SNTTPE = cast<SubstNonTypeTemplateParmExpr>(E);
4878  if (auto *CE = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(SNTTPE->getReplacement())) {
4879  // Pull out the constant value and mangle it as a template argument.
4880  QualType ParamType = SNTTPE->getParameterType(Context.getASTContext());
4881  assert(CE->hasAPValueResult() && "expected the NTTP to have an APValue");
4882  mangleValueInTemplateArg(ParamType, CE->getAPValueResult(), false,
4883  /*NeedExactType=*/true);
4884  break;
4885  }
4886  // The remaining cases all happen to be substituted with expressions that
4887  // mangle the same as a corresponding template argument anyway.
4888  E = cast<SubstNonTypeTemplateParmExpr>(E)->getReplacement();
4889  goto recurse;
4890  }
4891 
4892  case Expr::UserDefinedLiteralClass:
4893  // We follow g++'s approach of mangling a UDL as a call to the literal
4894  // operator.
4895  case Expr::CXXMemberCallExprClass: // fallthrough
4896  case Expr::CallExprClass: {
4897  NotPrimaryExpr();
4898  const CallExpr *CE = cast<CallExpr>(E);
4899 
4900  // <expression> ::= cp <simple-id> <expression>* E
4901  // We use this mangling only when the call would use ADL except
4902  // for being parenthesized. Per discussion with David
4903  // Vandervoorde, 2011.04.25.
4904  if (isParenthesizedADLCallee(CE)) {
4905  Out << "cp";
4906  // The callee here is a parenthesized UnresolvedLookupExpr with
4907  // no qualifier and should always get mangled as a <simple-id>
4908  // anyway.
4909 
4910  // <expression> ::= cl <expression>* E
4911  } else {
4912  Out << "cl";
4913  }
4914 
4915  unsigned CallArity = CE->getNumArgs();
4916  for (const Expr *Arg : CE->arguments())
4917  if (isa<PackExpansionExpr>(Arg))
4918  CallArity = UnknownArity;
4919 
4920  mangleExpression(CE->getCallee(), CallArity);
4921  for (const Expr *Arg : CE->arguments())
4922  mangleExpression(Arg);
4923  Out << 'E';
4924  break;
4925  }
4926 
4927  case Expr::CXXNewExprClass: {
4928  NotPrimaryExpr();
4929  const CXXNewExpr *New = cast<CXXNewExpr>(E);
4930  if (New->isGlobalNew()) Out << "gs";
4931  Out << (New->isArray() ? "na" : "nw");
4932  for (CXXNewExpr::const_arg_iterator I = New->placement_arg_begin(),
4933  E = New->placement_arg_end(); I != E; ++I)
4934  mangleExpression(*I);
4935  Out << '_';
4936  mangleType(New->getAllocatedType());
4937  if (New->hasInitializer()) {
4938  if (New->getInitializationStyle() == CXXNewInitializationStyle::Braces)
4939  Out << "il";
4940  else
4941  Out << "pi";
4942  const Expr *Init = New->getInitializer();
4943  if (const CXXConstructExpr *CCE = dyn_cast<CXXConstructExpr>(Init)) {
4944  // Directly inline the initializers.
4945  for (CXXConstructExpr::const_arg_iterator I = CCE->arg_begin(),
4946  E = CCE->arg_end();
4947  I != E; ++I)
4948  mangleExpression(*I);
4949  } else if (const ParenListExpr *PLE = dyn_cast<ParenListExpr>(Init)) {
4950  for (unsigned i = 0, e = PLE->getNumExprs(); i != e; ++i)
4951  mangleExpression(PLE->getExpr(i));
4952  } else if (New->getInitializationStyle() ==
4953  CXXNewInitializationStyle::Braces &&
4954  isa<InitListExpr>(Init)) {
4955  // Only take InitListExprs apart for list-initialization.
4956  mangleInitListElements(cast<InitListExpr>(Init));
4957  } else
4958  mangleExpression(Init);
4959  }
4960  Out << 'E';
4961  break;
4962  }
4963 
4964  case Expr::CXXPseudoDestructorExprClass: {
4965  NotPrimaryExpr();
4966  const auto *PDE = cast<CXXPseudoDestructorExpr>(E);
4967  if (const Expr *Base = PDE->getBase())
4968  mangleMemberExprBase(Base, PDE->isArrow());
4969  NestedNameSpecifier *Qualifier = PDE->getQualifier();
4970  if (TypeSourceInfo *ScopeInfo = PDE->getScopeTypeInfo()) {
4971  if (Qualifier) {
4972  mangleUnresolvedPrefix(Qualifier,
4973  /*recursive=*/true);
4974  mangleUnresolvedTypeOrSimpleId(ScopeInfo->getType());
4975  Out << 'E';
4976  } else {
4977  Out << "sr";
4978  if (!mangleUnresolvedTypeOrSimpleId(ScopeInfo->getType()))
4979  Out << 'E';
4980  }
4981  } else if (Qualifier) {
4982  mangleUnresolvedPrefix(Qualifier);
4983  }
4984  // <base-unresolved-name> ::= dn <destructor-name>
4985  Out << "dn";
4986  QualType DestroyedType = PDE->getDestroyedType();
4987  mangleUnresolvedTypeOrSimpleId(DestroyedType);
4988  break;
4989  }
4990 
4991  case Expr::MemberExprClass: {
4992  NotPrimaryExpr();
4993  const MemberExpr *ME = cast<MemberExpr>(E);
4994  mangleMemberExpr(ME->getBase(), ME->isArrow(),
4995  ME->getQualifier(), nullptr,
4996  ME->getMemberDecl()->getDeclName(),
4997  ME->getTemplateArgs(), ME->getNumTemplateArgs(),
4998  Arity);
4999  break;
5000  }
5001 
5002  case Expr::UnresolvedMemberExprClass: {
5003  NotPrimaryExpr();
5004  const UnresolvedMemberExpr *ME = cast<UnresolvedMemberExpr>(E);
5005  mangleMemberExpr(ME->isImplicitAccess() ? nullptr : ME->getBase(),
5006  ME->isArrow(), ME->getQualifier(), nullptr,
5007  ME->getMemberName(),
5008  ME->getTemplateArgs(), ME->getNumTemplateArgs(),
5009  Arity);
5010  break;
5011  }
5012 
5013  case Expr::CXXDependentScopeMemberExprClass: {
5014  NotPrimaryExpr();
5015  const CXXDependentScopeMemberExpr *ME
5016  = cast<CXXDependentScopeMemberExpr>(E);
5017  mangleMemberExpr(ME->isImplicitAccess() ? nullptr : ME->getBase(),
5018  ME->isArrow(), ME->getQualifier(),
5019  ME->getFirstQualifierFoundInScope(),
5020  ME->getMember(),
5021  ME->getTemplateArgs(), ME->getNumTemplateArgs(),
5022  Arity);
5023  break;
5024  }
5025 
5026  case Expr::UnresolvedLookupExprClass: {
5027  NotPrimaryExpr();
5028  const UnresolvedLookupExpr *ULE = cast<UnresolvedLookupExpr>(E);
5029  mangleUnresolvedName(ULE->getQualifier(), ULE->getName(),
5030  ULE->getTemplateArgs(), ULE->getNumTemplateArgs(),
5031  Arity);
5032  break;
5033  }
5034 
5035  case Expr::CXXUnresolvedConstructExprClass: {
5036  NotPrimaryExpr();
5037  const CXXUnresolvedConstructExpr *CE = cast<CXXUnresolvedConstructExpr>(E);
5038  unsigned N = CE->getNumArgs();
5039 
5040  if (CE->isListInitialization()) {
5041  assert(N == 1 && "unexpected form for list initialization");
5042  auto *IL = cast<InitListExpr>(CE->getArg(0));
5043  Out << "tl";
5044  mangleType(CE->getType());
5045  mangleInitListElements(IL);
5046  Out << "E";
5047  break;
5048  }
5049 
5050  Out << "cv";
5051  mangleType(CE->getType());
5052  if (N != 1) Out << '_';
5053  for (unsigned I = 0; I != N; ++I) mangleExpression(CE->getArg(I));
5054  if (N != 1) Out << 'E';
5055  break;
5056  }
5057 
5058  case Expr::CXXConstructExprClass: {
5059  // An implicit cast is silent, thus may contain <expr-primary>.
5060  const auto *CE = cast<CXXConstructExpr>(E);
5061  if (!CE->isListInitialization() || CE->isStdInitListInitialization()) {
5062  assert(
5063  CE->getNumArgs() >= 1 &&
5064  (CE->getNumArgs() == 1 || isa<CXXDefaultArgExpr>(CE->getArg(1))) &&
5065  "implicit CXXConstructExpr must have one argument");
5066  E = cast<CXXConstructExpr>(E)->getArg(0);
5067  goto recurse;
5068  }
5069  NotPrimaryExpr();
5070  Out << "il";
5071  for (auto *E : CE->arguments())
5072  mangleExpression(E);
5073  Out << "E";
5074  break;
5075  }
5076 
5077  case Expr::CXXTemporaryObjectExprClass: {
5078  NotPrimaryExpr();
5079  const auto *CE = cast<CXXTemporaryObjectExpr>(E);
5080  unsigned N = CE->getNumArgs();
5081  bool List = CE->isListInitialization();
5082 
5083  if (List)
5084  Out << "tl";
5085  else
5086  Out << "cv";
5087  mangleType(CE->getType());
5088  if (!List && N != 1)
5089  Out << '_';
5090  if (CE->isStdInitListInitialization()) {
5091  // We implicitly created a std::initializer_list<T> for the first argument
5092  // of a constructor of type U in an expression of the form U{a, b, c}.
5093  // Strip all the semantic gunk off the initializer list.
5094  auto *SILE =
5095  cast<CXXStdInitializerListExpr>(CE->getArg(0)->IgnoreImplicit());
5096  auto *ILE = cast<InitListExpr>(SILE->getSubExpr()->IgnoreImplicit());
5097  mangleInitListElements(ILE);
5098  } else {
5099  for (auto *E : CE->arguments())
5100  mangleExpression(E);
5101  }
5102  if (List || N != 1)
5103  Out << 'E';
5104  break;
5105  }
5106 
5107  case Expr::CXXScalarValueInitExprClass:
5108  NotPrimaryExpr();
5109  Out << "cv";
5110  mangleType(E->getType());
5111  Out << "_E";
5112  break;
5113 
5114  case Expr::CXXNoexceptExprClass:
5115  NotPrimaryExpr();
5116  Out << "nx";
5117  mangleExpression(cast<CXXNoexceptExpr>(E)->getOperand());
5118  break;
5119 
5120  case Expr::UnaryExprOrTypeTraitExprClass: {
5121  // Non-instantiation-dependent traits are an <expr-primary> integer literal.
5122  const UnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr *SAE = cast<UnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr>(E);
5123 
5124  if (!SAE->isInstantiationDependent()) {
5125  // Itanium C++ ABI:
5126  // If the operand of a sizeof or alignof operator is not
5127  // instantiation-dependent it is encoded as an integer literal
5128  // reflecting the result of the operator.
5129  //
5130  // If the result of the operator is implicitly converted to a known
5131  // integer type, that type is used for the literal; otherwise, the type
5132  // of std::size_t or std::ptrdiff_t is used.
5133  //
5134  // FIXME: We still include the operand in the profile in this case. This
5135  // can lead to mangling collisions between function templates that we
5136  // consider to be different.
5137  QualType T = (ImplicitlyConvertedToType.isNull() ||
5138  !ImplicitlyConvertedToType->isIntegerType())? SAE->getType()
5139  : ImplicitlyConvertedToType;
5140  llvm::APSInt V = SAE->EvaluateKnownConstInt(Context.getASTContext());
5141  mangleIntegerLiteral(T, V);
5142  break;
5143  }
5144 
5145  NotPrimaryExpr(); // But otherwise, they are not.
5146 
5147  auto MangleAlignofSizeofArg = [&] {
5148  if (SAE->isArgumentType()) {
5149  Out << 't';
5150  mangleType(SAE->getArgumentType());
5151  } else {
5152  Out << 'z';
5153  mangleExpression(SAE->getArgumentExpr());
5154  }
5155  };
5156 
5157  switch(SAE->getKind()) {
5158  case UETT_SizeOf:
5159  Out << 's';
5160  MangleAlignofSizeofArg();
5161  break;
5162  case UETT_PreferredAlignOf:
5163  // As of clang 12, we mangle __alignof__ differently than alignof. (They
5164  // have acted differently since Clang 8, but were previously mangled the
5165  // same.)
5166  if (!isCompatibleWith(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver11)) {
5167  Out << "u11__alignof__";
5168  if (SAE->isArgumentType())
5169  mangleType(SAE->getArgumentType());
5170  else
5171  mangleTemplateArgExpr(SAE->getArgumentExpr());
5172  Out << 'E';
5173  break;
5174  }
5175  [[fallthrough]];
5176  case UETT_AlignOf:
5177  Out << 'a';
5178  MangleAlignofSizeofArg();
5179  break;
5180  case UETT_DataSizeOf: {
5181  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags = Context.getDiags();
5182  unsigned DiagID =
5183  Diags.getCustomDiagID(DiagnosticsEngine::Error,
5184  "cannot yet mangle __datasizeof expression");
5185  Diags.Report(DiagID);
5186  return;
5187  }
5188  case UETT_VecStep: {
5189  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags = Context.getDiags();
5190  unsigned DiagID = Diags.getCustomDiagID(DiagnosticsEngine::Error,
5191  "cannot yet mangle vec_step expression");
5192  Diags.Report(DiagID);
5193  return;
5194  }
5195  case UETT_OpenMPRequiredSimdAlign: {
5196  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags = Context.getDiags();
5197  unsigned DiagID = Diags.getCustomDiagID(
5198  DiagnosticsEngine::Error,
5199  "cannot yet mangle __builtin_omp_required_simd_align expression");
5200  Diags.Report(DiagID);
5201  return;
5202  }
5203  case UETT_VectorElements: {
5204  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags = Context.getDiags();
5205  unsigned DiagID = Diags.getCustomDiagID(
5206  DiagnosticsEngine::Error,
5207  "cannot yet mangle __builtin_vectorelements expression");
5208  Diags.Report(DiagID);
5209  return;
5210  }
5211  }
5212  break;
5213  }
5214 
5215  case Expr::TypeTraitExprClass: {
5216  // <expression> ::= u <source-name> <template-arg>* E # vendor extension
5217  const TypeTraitExpr *TTE = cast<TypeTraitExpr>(E);
5218  NotPrimaryExpr();
5219  Out << 'u';
5220  llvm::StringRef Spelling = getTraitSpelling(TTE->getTrait());
5221  Out << Spelling.size() << Spelling;
5222  for (TypeSourceInfo *TSI : TTE->getArgs()) {
5223  mangleType(TSI->getType());
5224  }

5226  break;

5229  case Expr::CXXThrowExprClass: {
5230  NotPrimaryExpr();

5232  // <expression> ::= tw <expression> # throw expression
5233  // ::= tr # rethrow
5234  if (TE->getSubExpr()) {
5235  Out << "tw";
5236  mangleExpression(TE->getSubExpr());
5237  } else {
5238  Out << "tr";
5239  }

5243  case Expr::CXXTypeidExprClass: {
5244  NotPrimaryExpr();

5247  // ::= te <expression> # typeid (expression)
5248  if (TIE->isTypeOperand()) {
5249  Out << "ti";
5250  mangleType(TIE->getTypeOperand(Context.getASTContext()));
5251  } else {

5254  }

5258  case Expr::CXXDeleteExprClass: {

5261  // <expression> ::= [gs] dl <expression> # [::] delete expr

5265  mangleExpression(DE->getArgument());

5273  /*Arity=*/1);

5342  case Expr::ObjCBridgedCastExprClass: {

5357  case Expr::CXXFunctionalCastExprClass: {
5358  NotPrimaryExpr();
5359  auto *Sub = cast<ExplicitCastExpr>(E)->getSubExpr()->IgnoreImplicit();
5360  // FIXME: Add isImplicit to CXXConstructExpr.
5361  if (auto *CCE = dyn_cast<CXXConstructExpr>(Sub))
5362  if (CCE->getParenOrBraceRange().isInvalid())
5363  Sub = CCE->getArg(0)->IgnoreImplicit();
5364  if (auto *StdInitList = dyn_cast<CXXStdInitializerListExpr>(Sub))
5365  Sub = StdInitList->getSubExpr()->IgnoreImplicit();
5366  if (auto *IL = dyn_cast<InitListExpr>(Sub)) {
5367  Out << "tl";
5368  mangleType(E->getType());
5369  mangleInitListElements(IL);
5370  Out << "E";
5371  } else {
5372  mangleCastExpression(E, "cv");
5373  }
5374  break;
5375  }
5376 
5377  case Expr::CXXStaticCastExprClass:
5378  NotPrimaryExpr();
5379  mangleCastExpression(E, "sc");
5380  break;
5381  case Expr::CXXDynamicCastExprClass:
5382  NotPrimaryExpr();
5383  mangleCastExpression(E, "dc");
5384  break;
5385  case Expr::CXXReinterpretCastExprClass:
5386  NotPrimaryExpr();
5387  mangleCastExpression(E, "rc");
5388  break;
5389  case Expr::CXXConstCastExprClass:
5390  NotPrimaryExpr();
5391  mangleCastExpression(E, "cc");
5392  break;
5393  case Expr::CXXAddrspaceCastExprClass:
5394  NotPrimaryExpr();
5395  mangleCastExpression(E, "ac");
5396  break;
5397 
5398  case Expr::CXXOperatorCallExprClass: {
5399  NotPrimaryExpr();
5400  const CXXOperatorCallExpr *CE = cast<CXXOperatorCallExpr>(E);
5401  unsigned NumArgs = CE->getNumArgs();
5402  // A CXXOperatorCallExpr for OO_Arrow models only semantics, not syntax
5403  // (the enclosing MemberExpr covers the syntactic portion).
5404  if (CE->getOperator() != OO_Arrow)
5405  mangleOperatorName(CE->getOperator(), /*Arity=*/NumArgs);
5406  // Mangle the arguments.
5407  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumArgs; ++i)
5408  mangleExpression(CE->getArg(i));
5409  break;
5410  }
5411 
5412  case Expr::ParenExprClass:
5413  E = cast<ParenExpr>(E)->getSubExpr();
5414  goto recurse;
5415 
5416  case Expr::ConceptSpecializationExprClass: {
5417  auto *CSE = cast<ConceptSpecializationExpr>(E);
5418  if (isCompatibleWith(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver17)) {
5419  // Clang 17 and before mangled concept-ids as if they resolved to an
5420  // entity, meaning that references to enclosing template arguments don't
5421  // work.
5422  Out << "L_Z";
5423  mangleTemplateName(CSE->getNamedConcept(), CSE->getTemplateArguments());
5424  Out << 'E';
5425  break;
5426  }
5427  // Proposed on https://github.com/itanium-cxx-abi/cxx-abi/issues/24.
5428  NotPrimaryExpr();
5429  mangleUnresolvedName(
5430  CSE->getNestedNameSpecifierLoc().getNestedNameSpecifier(),
5431  CSE->getConceptNameInfo().getName(),
5432  CSE->getTemplateArgsAsWritten()->getTemplateArgs(),
5433  CSE->getTemplateArgsAsWritten()->getNumTemplateArgs());
5434  break;
5435  }
5436 
5437  case Expr::RequiresExprClass: {
5438  // Proposed on https://github.com/itanium-cxx-abi/cxx-abi/issues/24.
5439  auto *RE = cast<RequiresExpr>(E);
5440  // This is a primary-expression in the C++ grammar, but does not have an
5441  // <expr-primary> mangling (starting with 'L').
5442  NotPrimaryExpr();
5443  if (RE->getLParenLoc().isValid()) {
5444  Out << "rQ";
5445  FunctionTypeDepthState saved = FunctionTypeDepth.push();
5446  if (RE->getLocalParameters().empty()) {
5447  Out << 'v';
5448  } else {
5449  for (ParmVarDecl *Param : RE->getLocalParameters()) {
5450  mangleType(Context.getASTContext().getSignatureParameterType(
5451  Param->getType()));
5452  }
5453  }
5454  Out << '_';
5455 
5456  // The rest of the mangling is in the immediate scope of the parameters.
5457  FunctionTypeDepth.enterResultType();
5458  for (const concepts::Requirement *Req : RE->getRequirements())
5459  mangleRequirement(RE->getExprLoc(), Req);
5460  FunctionTypeDepth.pop(saved);
5461  Out << 'E';
5462  } else {
5463  Out << "rq";
5464  for (const concepts::Requirement *Req : RE->getRequirements())
5465  mangleRequirement(RE->getExprLoc(), Req);
5466  Out << 'E';
5467  }
5468  break;
5469  }
5470 
5471  case Expr::DeclRefExprClass:
5472  // MangleDeclRefExpr helper handles primary-vs-nonprimary
5473  MangleDeclRefExpr(cast<DeclRefExpr>(E)->getDecl());
5474  break;
5475 
5476  case Expr::SubstNonTypeTemplateParmPackExprClass:
5477  NotPrimaryExpr();
5478  // FIXME: not clear how to mangle this!
5479  // template <unsigned N...> class A {
5480  // template <class U...> void foo(U (&x)[N]...);
5481  // };
5482  Out << "_SUBSTPACK_";
5483  break;
5484 
5485  case Expr::FunctionParmPackExprClass: {
5486  NotPrimaryExpr();
5487  // FIXME: not clear how to mangle this!
5488  const FunctionParmPackExpr *FPPE = cast<FunctionParmPackExpr>(E);
5489  Out << "v110_SUBSTPACK";
5490  MangleDeclRefExpr(FPPE->getParameterPack());
5491  break;
5492  }
5493 
5494  case Expr::DependentScopeDeclRefExprClass: {
5495  NotPrimaryExpr();
5496  const DependentScopeDeclRefExpr *DRE = cast<DependentScopeDeclRefExpr>(E);
5497  mangleUnresolvedName(DRE->getQualifier(), DRE->getDeclName(),
5498  DRE->getTemplateArgs(), DRE->getNumTemplateArgs(),
5499  Arity);
5500  break;
5501  }
5502 
5503  case Expr::CXXBindTemporaryExprClass:
5504  E = cast<CXXBindTemporaryExpr>(E)->getSubExpr();
5505  goto recurse;
5506 
5507  case Expr::ExprWithCleanupsClass:
5508  E = cast<ExprWithCleanups>(E)->getSubExpr();
5509  goto recurse;
5510 
5511  case Expr::FloatingLiteralClass: {
5512  // <expr-primary>
5513  const FloatingLiteral *FL = cast<FloatingLiteral>(E);
5514  mangleFloatLiteral(FL->getType(), FL->getValue());
5515  break;
5516  }
5517 
5518  case Expr::FixedPointLiteralClass:
5519  // Currently unimplemented -- might be <expr-primary> in future?
5520  mangleFixedPointLiteral();
5521  break;
5522 
5523  case Expr::CharacterLiteralClass:
5524  // <expr-primary>
5525  Out << 'L';
5526  mangleType(E->getType());
5527  Out << cast<CharacterLiteral>(E)->getValue();
5528  Out << 'E';
5529  break;
5530 
5531  // FIXME. __objc_yes/__objc_no are mangled same as true/false
5532  case Expr::ObjCBoolLiteralExprClass:
5533  // <expr-primary>
5534  Out << "Lb";
5535  Out << (cast<ObjCBoolLiteralExpr>(E)->getValue() ? '1' : '0');
5536  Out << 'E';
5537  break;
5538 
5539  case Expr::CXXBoolLiteralExprClass:
5540  // <expr-primary>
5541  Out << "Lb";
5542  Out << (cast<CXXBoolLiteralExpr>(E)->getValue() ? '1' : '0');
5543  Out << 'E';
5544  break;
5545 
5546  case Expr::IntegerLiteralClass: {
5547  // <expr-primary>
5548  llvm::APSInt Value(cast<IntegerLiteral>(E)->getValue());
5549  if (E->getType()->isSignedIntegerType())
5550  Value.setIsSigned(true);
5551  mangleIntegerLiteral(E->getType(), Value);
5552  break;
5553  }
5554 
5555  case Expr::ImaginaryLiteralClass: {
5556  // <expr-primary>
5557  const ImaginaryLiteral *IE = cast<ImaginaryLiteral>(E);
5558  // Mangle as if a complex literal.
5559  // Proposal from David Vandevoorde, 2010.06.30.
5560  Out << 'L';
5561  mangleType(E->getType());
5562  if (const FloatingLiteral *Imag =
5563  dyn_cast<FloatingLiteral>(IE->getSubExpr())) {
5564  // Mangle a floating-point zero of the appropriate type.
5565  mangleFloat(llvm::APFloat(Imag->getValue().getSemantics()));
5566  Out << '_';
5567  mangleFloat(Imag->getValue());
5568  } else {
5569  Out << "0_";
5570  llvm::APSInt Value(cast<IntegerLiteral>(IE->getSubExpr())->getValue());
5571  if (IE->getSubExpr()->getType()->isSignedIntegerType())
5572  Value.setIsSigned(true);
5573  mangleNumber(Value);
5574  }
5575  Out << 'E';
5576  break;
5577  }
5578 
5579  case Expr::StringLiteralClass: {
5580  // <expr-primary>
5581  // Revised proposal from David Vandervoorde, 2010.07.15.
5582  Out << 'L';
5583  assert(isa<ConstantArrayType>(E->getType()));
5584  mangleType(E->getType());
5585  Out << 'E';
5586  break;
5587  }
5588 
5589  case Expr::GNUNullExprClass:
5590  // <expr-primary>
5591  // Mangle as if an integer literal 0.
5592  mangleIntegerLiteral(E->getType(), llvm::APSInt(32));
5593  break;
5594 
5595  case Expr::CXXNullPtrLiteralExprClass: {
5596  // <expr-primary>
5597  Out << "LDnE";
5598  break;
5599  }
5600 
5601  case Expr::LambdaExprClass: {
5602  // A lambda-expression can't appear in the signature of an
5603  // externally-visible declaration, so there's no standard mangling for
5604  // this, but mangling as a literal of the closure type seems reasonable.
5605  Out << "L";
5606  mangleType(Context.getASTContext().getRecordType(cast<LambdaExpr>(E)->getLambdaClass()));
5607  Out << "E";
5608  break;
5609  }
5610 
5611  case Expr::PackExpansionExprClass:
5612  NotPrimaryExpr();
5613  Out << "sp";
5614  mangleExpression(cast<PackExpansionExpr>(E)->getPattern());
5615  break;
5616 
5617  case Expr::SizeOfPackExprClass: {
5618  NotPrimaryExpr();
5619  auto *SPE = cast<SizeOfPackExpr>(E);
5620  if (SPE->isPartiallySubstituted()) {
5621  Out << "sP";
5622  for (const auto &A : SPE->getPartialArguments())
5623  mangleTemplateArg(A, false);
5624  Out << "E";
5625  break;
5626  }
5627 
5628  Out << "sZ";
5629  const NamedDecl *Pack = SPE->getPack();
5630  if (const TemplateTypeParmDecl *TTP = dyn_cast<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(Pack))
5631  mangleTemplateParameter(TTP->getDepth(), TTP->getIndex());
5632  else if (const NonTypeTemplateParmDecl *NTTP
5633  = dyn_cast<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(Pack))
5634  mangleTemplateParameter(NTTP->getDepth(), NTTP->getIndex());
5635  else if (const TemplateTemplateParmDecl *TempTP
5636  = dyn_cast<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(Pack))
5637  mangleTemplateParameter(TempTP->getDepth(), TempTP->getIndex());
5638  else
5639  mangleFunctionParam(cast<ParmVarDecl>(Pack));
5640  break;
5641  }
5642 
5643  case Expr::MaterializeTemporaryExprClass:
5644  E = cast<MaterializeTemporaryExpr>(E)->getSubExpr();
5645  goto recurse;
5646 
5647  case Expr::CXXFoldExprClass: {
5648  NotPrimaryExpr();
5649  auto *FE = cast<CXXFoldExpr>(E);
5650  if (FE->isLeftFold())
5651  Out << (FE->getInit() ? "fL" : "fl");
5652  else
5653  Out << (FE->getInit() ? "fR" : "fr");
5654 
5655  if (FE->getOperator() == BO_PtrMemD)
5656  Out << "ds";
5657  else
5658  mangleOperatorName(
5659  BinaryOperator::getOverloadedOperator(FE->getOperator()),
5660  /*Arity=*/2);
5661 
5662  if (FE->getLHS())
5663  mangleExpression(FE->getLHS());
5664  if (FE->getRHS())
5665  mangleExpression(FE->getRHS());
5666  break;
5667  }
5668 
5669  case Expr::CXXThisExprClass:
5670  NotPrimaryExpr();
5671  Out << "fpT";
5672  break;
5673 
5674  case Expr::CoawaitExprClass:
5675  // FIXME: Propose a non-vendor mangling.
5676  NotPrimaryExpr();
5677  Out << "v18co_await";
5678  mangleExpression(cast<CoawaitExpr>(E)->getOperand());
5679  break;
5680 
5681  case Expr::DependentCoawaitExprClass:
5682  // FIXME: Propose a non-vendor mangling.
5683  NotPrimaryExpr();
5684  Out << "v18co_await";
5685  mangleExpression(cast<DependentCoawaitExpr>(E)->getOperand());
5686  break;
5687 
5688  case Expr::CoyieldExprClass:
5689  // FIXME: Propose a non-vendor mangling.
5690  NotPrimaryExpr();
5691  Out << "v18co_yield";
5692  mangleExpression(cast<CoawaitExpr>(E)->getOperand());
5693  break;
5694  case Expr::SYCLUniqueStableNameExprClass: {
5695  const auto *USN = cast<SYCLUniqueStableNameExpr>(E);
5696  NotPrimaryExpr();
5697 
5698  Out << "u33__builtin_sycl_unique_stable_name";
5699  mangleType(USN->getTypeSourceInfo()->getType());
5700 
5701  Out << "E";
5702  break;
5703  }
5704  case Expr::SYCLUniqueStableIdExprClass: {
5705  const auto *USID = cast<SYCLUniqueStableIdExpr>(E);
5706  NotPrimaryExpr();
5707 
5708  Out << "cl31__builtin_sycl_unique_stable_id";
5709  mangleExpression(USID->getExpr());
5710  Out << "E";
5711  break;
5712  }
5713  }
5714 
5715  if (AsTemplateArg && !IsPrimaryExpr)
5716  Out << 'E';
5717 }
5718 
5719 /// Mangle an expression which refers to a parameter variable.
5720 ///
5721 /// <expression> ::= <function-param>
5722 /// <function-param> ::= fp <top-level CV-qualifiers> _ # L == 0, I == 0
5723 /// <function-param> ::= fp <top-level CV-qualifiers>
5724 /// <parameter-2 non-negative number> _ # L == 0, I > 0
5725 /// <function-param> ::= fL <L-1 non-negative number>
5726 /// p <top-level CV-qualifiers> _ # L > 0, I == 0
5727 /// <function-param> ::= fL <L-1 non-negative number>
5728 /// p <top-level CV-qualifiers>
5729 /// <I-1 non-negative number> _ # L > 0, I > 0
5730 ///
5731 /// L is the nesting depth of the parameter, defined as 1 if the
5732 /// parameter comes from the innermost function prototype scope
5733 /// enclosing the current context, 2 if from the next enclosing
5734 /// function prototype scope, and so on, with one special case: if
5735 /// we've processed the full parameter clause for the innermost
5736 /// function type, then L is one less. This definition conveniently
5737 /// makes it irrelevant whether a function's result type was written
5738 /// trailing or leading, but is otherwise overly complicated; the
5739 /// numbering was first designed without considering references to
5740 /// parameter in locations other than return types, and then the
5741 /// mangling had to be generalized without changing the existing
5742 /// manglings.
5743 ///
5744 /// I is the zero-based index of the parameter within its parameter
5745 /// declaration clause. Note that the original ABI document describes
5746 /// this using 1-based ordinals.
5747 void CXXNameMangler::mangleFunctionParam(const ParmVarDecl *parm) {
5748  unsigned parmDepth = parm->getFunctionScopeDepth();
5749  unsigned parmIndex = parm->getFunctionScopeIndex();
5750 
5751  // Compute 'L'.
5752  // parmDepth does not include the declaring function prototype.
5753  // FunctionTypeDepth does account for that.
5754  assert(parmDepth < FunctionTypeDepth.getDepth());
5755  unsigned nestingDepth = FunctionTypeDepth.getDepth() - parmDepth;
5756  if (FunctionTypeDepth.isInResultType())
5757  nestingDepth--;
5758 
5759  if (nestingDepth == 0) {
5760  Out << "fp";
5761  } else {
5762  Out << "fL" << (nestingDepth - 1) << 'p';
5763  }
5764 
5765  // Top-level qualifiers. We don't have to worry about arrays here,
5766  // because parameters declared as arrays should already have been
5767  // transformed to have pointer type. FIXME: apparently these don't
5768  // get mangled if used as an rvalue of a known non-class type?
5769  assert(!parm->getType()->isArrayType()
5770  && "parameter's type is still an array type?");
5771 
5772  if (const DependentAddressSpaceType *DAST =
5773  dyn_cast<DependentAddressSpaceType>(parm->getType())) {
5774  mangleQualifiers(DAST->getPointeeType().getQualifiers(), DAST);
5775  } else {
5776  mangleQualifiers(parm->getType().getQualifiers());
5777  }
5778 
5779  // Parameter index.
5780  if (parmIndex != 0) {
5781  Out << (parmIndex - 1);
5782  }
5783  Out << '_';
5784 }
5785 
5786 void CXXNameMangler::mangleCXXCtorType(CXXCtorType T,
5787  const CXXRecordDecl *InheritedFrom) {
5788  // <ctor-dtor-name> ::= C1 # complete object constructor
5789  // ::= C2 # base object constructor
5790  // ::= CI1 <type> # complete inheriting constructor
5791  // ::= CI2 <type> # base inheriting constructor
5792  //
5793  // In addition, C5 is a comdat name with C1 and C2 in it.
5794  Out << 'C';
5795  if (InheritedFrom)
5796  Out << 'I';
5797  switch (T) {
5798  case Ctor_Complete:
5799  Out << '1';
5800  break;
5801  case Ctor_Base:
5802  Out << '2';
5803  break;
5804  case Ctor_Comdat:
5805  Out << '5';
5806  break;
5807  case Ctor_DefaultClosure:
5808  case Ctor_CopyingClosure:
5809  llvm_unreachable("closure constructors don't exist for the Itanium ABI!");
5810  }
5811  if (InheritedFrom)
5812  mangleName(InheritedFrom);
5813 }
5814 
5815 void CXXNameMangler::mangleCXXDtorType(CXXDtorType T) {
5816  // <ctor-dtor-name> ::= D0 # deleting destructor
5817  // ::= D1 # complete object destructor
5818  // ::= D2 # base object destructor
5819  //
5820  // In addition, D5 is a comdat name with D1, D2 and, if virtual, D0 in it.
5821  switch (T) {
5822  case Dtor_Deleting:
5823  Out << "D0";
5824  break;
5825  case Dtor_Complete:
5826  Out << "D1";
5827  break;
5828  case Dtor_Base:
5829  Out << "D2";
5830  break;
5831  case Dtor_Comdat:
5832  Out << "D5";
5833  break;
5834  }
5835 }
5836 
5837 // Helper to provide ancillary information on a template used to mangle its
5838 // arguments.
5839 struct CXXNameMangler::TemplateArgManglingInfo {
5840  const CXXNameMangler &Mangler;
5841  TemplateDecl *ResolvedTemplate = nullptr;
5842  bool SeenPackExpansionIntoNonPack = false;
5843  const NamedDecl *UnresolvedExpandedPack = nullptr;
5844 
5845  TemplateArgManglingInfo(const CXXNameMangler &Mangler, TemplateName TN)
5846  : Mangler(Mangler) {
5847  if (TemplateDecl *TD = TN.getAsTemplateDecl())
5848  ResolvedTemplate = TD;
5849  }
5850 
5851  /// Information about how to mangle a template argument.
5852  struct Info {
5853  /// Do we need to mangle the template argument with an exactly correct type?
5854  bool NeedExactType;
5855  /// If we need to prefix the mangling with a mangling of the template
5856  /// parameter, the corresponding parameter.
5857  const NamedDecl *TemplateParameterToMangle;
5858  };
5859 
5860  /// Determine whether the resolved template might be overloaded on its
5861  /// template parameter list. If so, the mangling needs to include enough
5862  /// information to reconstruct the template parameter list.
5863  bool isOverloadable() {
5864  // Function templates are generally overloadable. As a special case, a
5865  // member function template of a generic lambda is not overloadable.
5866  if (auto *FTD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionTemplateDecl>(ResolvedTemplate)) {
5867  auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(FTD->getDeclContext());
5868  if (!RD || !RD->isGenericLambda())
5869  return true;
5870  }
5871 
5872  // All other templates are not overloadable. Partial specializations would
5873  // be, but we never mangle them.
5874  return false;
5875  }
5876 
5877  /// Determine whether we need to prefix this <template-arg> mangling with a
5878  /// <template-param-decl>. This happens if the natural template parameter for
5879  /// the argument mangling is not the same as the actual template parameter.
5880  bool needToMangleTemplateParam(const NamedDecl *Param,
5881  const TemplateArgument &Arg) {
5882  // For a template type parameter, the natural parameter is 'typename T'.
5883  // The actual parameter might be constrained.
5884  if (auto *TTP = dyn_cast<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(Param))
5885  return TTP->hasTypeConstraint();
5886 
5887  if (Arg.getKind() == TemplateArgument::Pack) {
5888  // For an empty pack, the natural parameter is `typename...`.
5889  if (Arg.pack_size() == 0)
5890  return true;
5891 
5892  // For any other pack, we use the first argument to determine the natural
5893  // template parameter.
5894  return needToMangleTemplateParam(Param, *Arg.pack_begin());
5895  }
5896 
5897  // For a non-type template parameter, the natural parameter is `T V` (for a
5898  // prvalue argument) or `T &V` (for a glvalue argument), where `T` is the
5899  // type of the argument, which we require to exactly match. If the actual
5900  // parameter has a deduced or instantiation-dependent type, it is not
5901  // equivalent to the natural parameter.
5902  if (auto *NTTP = dyn_cast<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(Param))
5903  return NTTP->getType()->isInstantiationDependentType() ||
5904  NTTP->getType()->getContainedDeducedType();
5905 
5906  // For a template template parameter, the template-head might differ from
5907  // that of the template.
5908  auto *TTP = cast<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(Param);
5909  TemplateName ArgTemplateName = Arg.getAsTemplateOrTemplatePattern();
5910  const TemplateDecl *ArgTemplate = ArgTemplateName.getAsTemplateDecl();
5911  if (!ArgTemplate)
5912  return true;
5913 
5914  // Mangle the template parameter list of the parameter and argument to see
5915  // if they are the same. We can't use Profile for this, because it can't
5916  // model the depth difference between parameter and argument and might not
5917  // necessarily have the same definition of "identical" that we use here --
5918  // that is, same mangling.
5919  auto MangleTemplateParamListToString =
5920  [&](SmallVectorImpl<char> &Buffer, const TemplateParameterList *Params,
5921  unsigned DepthOffset) {
5922  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Stream(Buffer);
5923  CXXNameMangler(Mangler.Context, Stream,
5924  WithTemplateDepthOffset{DepthOffset})
5925  .mangleTemplateParameterList(Params);
5926  };
5927  llvm::SmallString<128> ParamTemplateHead, ArgTemplateHead;
5928  MangleTemplateParamListToString(ParamTemplateHead,
5929  TTP->getTemplateParameters(), 0);
5930  // Add the depth of the parameter's template parameter list to all
5931  // parameters appearing in the argument to make the indexes line up
5932  // properly.
5933  MangleTemplateParamListToString(ArgTemplateHead,
5934  ArgTemplate->getTemplateParameters(),
5935  TTP->getTemplateParameters()->getDepth());
5936  return ParamTemplateHead != ArgTemplateHead;
5937  }
5938 
5939  /// Determine information about how this template argument should be mangled.
5940  /// This should be called exactly once for each parameter / argument pair, in
5941  /// order.
5942  Info getArgInfo(unsigned ParamIdx, const TemplateArgument &Arg) {
5943  // We need correct types when the template-name is unresolved or when it
5944  // names a template that is able to be overloaded.
5945  if (!ResolvedTemplate || SeenPackExpansionIntoNonPack)
5946  return {true, nullptr};
5947 
5948  // Move to the next parameter.
5949  const NamedDecl *Param = UnresolvedExpandedPack;
5950  if (!Param) {
5951  assert(ParamIdx < ResolvedTemplate->getTemplateParameters()->size() &&
5952  "no parameter for argument");
5953  Param = ResolvedTemplate->getTemplateParameters()->getParam(ParamIdx);
5954 
5955  // If we reach a parameter pack whose argument isn't in pack form, that
5956  // means Sema couldn't or didn't figure out which arguments belonged to
5957  // it, because it contains a pack expansion or because Sema bailed out of
5958  // computing parameter / argument correspondence before this point. Track
5959  // the pack as the corresponding parameter for all further template
5960  // arguments until we hit a pack expansion, at which point we don't know
5961  // the correspondence between parameters and arguments at all.
5962  if (Param->isParameterPack() && Arg.getKind() != TemplateArgument::Pack) {
5963  UnresolvedExpandedPack = Param;
5964  }
5965  }
5966 
5967  // If we encounter a pack argument that is expanded into a non-pack
5968  // parameter, we can no longer track parameter / argument correspondence,
5969  // and need to use exact types from this point onwards.
5970  if (Arg.isPackExpansion() &&
5971  (!Param->isParameterPack() || UnresolvedExpandedPack)) {
5972  SeenPackExpansionIntoNonPack = true;
5973  return {true, nullptr};
5974  }
5975 
5976  // We need exact types for arguments of a template that might be overloaded
5977  // on template parameter type.
5978  if (isOverloadable())
5979  return {true, needToMangleTemplateParam(Param, Arg) ? Param : nullptr};
5980 
5981  // Otherwise, we only need a correct type if the parameter has a deduced
5982  // type.
5983  //
5984  // Note: for an expanded parameter pack, getType() returns the type prior
5985  // to expansion. We could ask for the expanded type with getExpansionType(),
5986  // but it doesn't matter because substitution and expansion don't affect
5987  // whether a deduced type appears in the type.
5988  auto *NTTP = dyn_cast<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(Param);
5989  bool NeedExactType = NTTP && NTTP->getType()->getContainedDeducedType();
5990  return {NeedExactType, nullptr};
5991  }
5992 
5993  /// Determine if we should mangle a requires-clause after the template
5994  /// argument list. If so, returns the expression to mangle.
5995  const Expr *getTrailingRequiresClauseToMangle() {
5996  if (!isOverloadable())
5997  return nullptr;
5998  return ResolvedTemplate->getTemplateParameters()->getRequiresClause();
5999  }
6000 };
6001 
6002 void CXXNameMangler::mangleTemplateArgs(TemplateName TN,
6003  const TemplateArgumentLoc *TemplateArgs,
6004  unsigned NumTemplateArgs) {
6005  // <template-args> ::= I <template-arg>+ [Q <requires-clause expr>] E
6006  Out << 'I';
6007  TemplateArgManglingInfo Info(*this, TN);
6008  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumTemplateArgs; ++i) {
6009  mangleTemplateArg(Info, i, TemplateArgs[i].getArgument());
6010  }
6011  mangleRequiresClause(Info.getTrailingRequiresClauseToMangle());
6012  Out << 'E';
6013 }
6014 
6015 void CXXNameMangler::mangleTemplateArgs(TemplateName TN,
6016  const TemplateArgumentList &AL) {
6017  // <template-args> ::= I <template-arg>+ [Q <requires-clause expr>] E
6018  Out << 'I';
6019  TemplateArgManglingInfo Info(*this, TN);
6020  for (unsigned i = 0, e = AL.size(); i != e; ++i) {
6021  mangleTemplateArg(Info, i, AL[i]);
6022  }
6023  mangleRequiresClause(Info.getTrailingRequiresClauseToMangle());
6024  Out << 'E';
6025 }
6026 
6027 void CXXNameMangler::mangleTemplateArgs(TemplateName TN,
6028  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args) {
6029  // <template-args> ::= I <template-arg>+ [Q <requires-clause expr>] E
6030  Out << 'I';
6031  TemplateArgManglingInfo Info(*this, TN);
6032  for (unsigned i = 0; i != Args.size(); ++i) {
6033  mangleTemplateArg(Info, i, Args[i]);
6034  }
6035  mangleRequiresClause(Info.getTrailingRequiresClauseToMangle());
6036  Out << 'E';
6037 }
6038 
6039 void CXXNameMangler::mangleTemplateArg(TemplateArgManglingInfo &Info,
6040  unsigned Index, TemplateArgument A) {
6041  TemplateArgManglingInfo::Info ArgInfo = Info.getArgInfo(Index, A);
6042 
6043  // Proposed on https://github.com/itanium-cxx-abi/cxx-abi/issues/47.
6044  if (ArgInfo.TemplateParameterToMangle &&
6045  !isCompatibleWith(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver17)) {
6046  // The template parameter is mangled if the mangling would otherwise be
6047  // ambiguous.
6048  //
6049  // <template-arg> ::= <template-param-decl> <template-arg>
6050  //
6051  // Clang 17 and before did not do this.
6052  mangleTemplateParamDecl(ArgInfo.TemplateParameterToMangle);
6053  }
6054 
6055  mangleTemplateArg(A, ArgInfo.NeedExactType);
6056 }
6057 
6058 void CXXNameMangler::mangleTemplateArg(TemplateArgument A, bool NeedExactType) {
6059  // <template-arg> ::= <type> # type or template
6060  // ::= X <expression> E # expression
6061  // ::= <expr-primary> # simple expressions
6062  // ::= J <template-arg>* E # argument pack
6063  if (!A.isInstantiationDependent() || A.isDependent())
6064  A = Context.getASTContext().getCanonicalTemplateArgument(A);
6065 
6066  switch (A.getKind()) {
6067  case TemplateArgument::Null:
6068  llvm_unreachable("Cannot mangle NULL template argument");
6069 
6070  case TemplateArgument::Type:
6071  mangleType(A.getAsType());
6072  break;
6073  case TemplateArgument::Template:
6074  // This is mangled as <type>.
6075  mangleType(A.getAsTemplate());
6076  break;
6077  case TemplateArgument::TemplateExpansion:
6078  // <type> ::= Dp <type> # pack expansion (C++0x)
6079  Out << "Dp";
6080  mangleType(A.getAsTemplateOrTemplatePattern());
6081  break;
6082  case TemplateArgument::Expression:
6083  mangleTemplateArgExpr(A.getAsExpr());
6084  break;
6085  case TemplateArgument::Integral:
6086  mangleIntegerLiteral(A.getIntegralType(), A.getAsIntegral());
6087  break;
6088  case TemplateArgument::Declaration: {
6089  // <expr-primary> ::= L <mangled-name> E # external name
6090  ValueDecl *D = A.getAsDecl();
6091 
6092  // Template parameter objects are modeled by reproducing a source form
6093  // produced as if by aggregate initialization.
6094  if (A.getParamTypeForDecl()->isRecordType()) {
6095  auto *TPO = cast<TemplateParamObjectDecl>(D);
6096  mangleValueInTemplateArg(TPO->getType().getUnqualifiedType(),
6097  TPO->getValue(), /*TopLevel=*/true,
6098  NeedExactType);
6099  break;
6100  }
6101 
6102  ASTContext &Ctx = Context.getASTContext();
6103  APValue Value;
6104  if (D->isCXXInstanceMember())
6105  // Simple pointer-to-member with no conversion.
6106  Value = APValue(D, /*IsDerivedMember=*/false, /*Path=*/{});
6107  else if (D->getType()->isArrayType() &&
6108  Ctx.hasSimilarType(Ctx.getDecayedType(D->getType()),
6109  A.getParamTypeForDecl()) &&
6110  !isCompatibleWith(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver11))
6111  // Build a value corresponding to this implicit array-to-pointer decay.
6112  Value = APValue(APValue::LValueBase(D), CharUnits::Zero(),
6113  {APValue::LValuePathEntry::ArrayIndex(0)},
6114  /*OnePastTheEnd=*/false);
6115  else
6116  // Regular pointer or reference to a declaration.
6117  Value = APValue(APValue::LValueBase(D), CharUnits::Zero(),
6118  ArrayRef<APValue::LValuePathEntry>(),
6119  /*OnePastTheEnd=*/false);
6120  mangleValueInTemplateArg(A.getParamTypeForDecl(), Value, /*TopLevel=*/true,
6121  NeedExactType);
6122  break;
6123  }
6124  case TemplateArgument::NullPtr: {
6125  mangleNullPointer(A.getNullPtrType());
6126  break;
6127  }
6128  case TemplateArgument::StructuralValue:
6129  mangleValueInTemplateArg(A.getStructuralValueType(),
6130  A.getAsStructuralValue(),
6131  /*TopLevel=*/true, NeedExactType);
6132  break;
6133  case TemplateArgument::Pack: {
6134  // <template-arg> ::= J <template-arg>* E
6135  Out << 'J';
6136  for (const auto &P : A.pack_elements())
6137  mangleTemplateArg(P, NeedExactType);
6138  Out << 'E';
6139  }
6140  }
6141 }
6142 
6143 void CXXNameMangler::mangleTemplateArgExpr(const Expr *E) {
6144  if (!isCompatibleWith(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver11)) {
6145  mangleExpression(E, UnknownArity, /*AsTemplateArg=*/true);
6146  return;
6147  }
6148 
6149  // Prior to Clang 12, we didn't omit the X .. E around <expr-primary>
6150  // correctly in cases where the template argument was
6151  // constructed from an expression rather than an already-evaluated
6152  // literal. In such a case, we would then e.g. emit 'XLi0EE' instead of
6153  // 'Li0E'.
6154  //
6155  // We did special-case DeclRefExpr to attempt to DTRT for that one
6156  // expression-kind, but while doing so, unfortunately handled ParmVarDecl
6157  // (subtype of VarDecl) _incorrectly_, and emitted 'L_Z .. E' instead of
6158  // the proper 'Xfp_E'.
6159  E = E->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
6160  if (const DeclRefExpr *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E)) {
6161  const ValueDecl *D = DRE->getDecl();
6162  if (isa<VarDecl>(D) || isa<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
6163  Out << 'L';
6164  mangle(D);
6165  Out << 'E';
6166  return;
6167  }
6168  }
6169  Out << 'X';
6170  mangleExpression(E);
6171  Out << 'E';
6172 }
6173 
6174 /// Determine whether a given value is equivalent to zero-initialization for
6175 /// the purpose of discarding a trailing portion of a 'tl' mangling.
6176 ///
6177 /// Note that this is not in general equivalent to determining whether the
6178 /// value has an all-zeroes bit pattern.
6179 static bool isZeroInitialized(QualType T, const APValue &V) {
6180  // FIXME: mangleValueInTemplateArg has quadratic time complexity in
6181  // pathological cases due to using this, but it's a little awkward
6182  // to do this in linear time in general.
6183  switch (V.getKind()) {
6184  case APValue::None:
6185  case APValue::Indeterminate:
6186  case APValue::AddrLabelDiff:
6187  return false;
6188 
6189  case APValue::Struct: {
6190  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
6191  assert(RD && "unexpected type for record value");
6192  unsigned I = 0;
6193  for (const CXXBaseSpecifier &BS : RD->bases()) {
6194  if (!isZeroInitialized(BS.getType(), V.getStructBase(I)))
6195  return false;
6196  ++I;
6197  }
6198  I = 0;
6199  for (const FieldDecl *FD : RD->fields()) {
6200  if (!FD->isUnnamedBitField() &&
6201  !isZeroInitialized(FD->getType(), V.getStructField(I)))
6202  return false;
6203  ++I;
6204  }
6205  return true;
6206  }
6207 
6208  case APValue::Union: {
6209  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
6210  assert(RD && "unexpected type for union value");
6211  // Zero-initialization zeroes the first non-unnamed-bitfield field, if any.
6212  for (const FieldDecl *FD : RD->fields()) {
6213  if (!FD->isUnnamedBitField())
6214  return V.getUnionField() && declaresSameEntity(FD, V.getUnionField()) &&
6215  isZeroInitialized(FD->getType(), V.getUnionValue());
6216  }
6217  // If there are no fields (other than unnamed bitfields), the value is
6218  // necessarily zero-initialized.
6219  return true;
6220  }
6221 
6222  case APValue::Array: {
6223  QualType ElemT(T->getArrayElementTypeNoTypeQual(), 0);
6224  for (unsigned I = 0, N = V.getArrayInitializedElts(); I != N; ++I)
6225  if (!isZeroInitialized(ElemT, V.getArrayInitializedElt(I)))
6226  return false;
6227  return !V.hasArrayFiller() || isZeroInitialized(ElemT, V.getArrayFiller());
6228  }
6229 
6230  case APValue::Vector: {
6231  const VectorType *VT = T->castAs<VectorType>();
6232  for (unsigned I = 0, N = V.getVectorLength(); I != N; ++I)
6233  if (!isZeroInitialized(VT->getElementType(), V.getVectorElt(I)))
6234  return false;
6235  return true;
6236  }
6237 
6238  case APValue::Int:
6239  return !V.getInt();
6240 
6241  case APValue::Float:
6242  return V.getFloat().isPosZero();
6243 
6244  case APValue::FixedPoint:
6245  return !V.getFixedPoint().getValue();
6246 
6247  case APValue::ComplexFloat:
6248  return V.getComplexFloatReal().isPosZero() &&
6249  V.getComplexFloatImag().isPosZero();
6250 
6251  case APValue::ComplexInt:
6252  return !V.getComplexIntReal() && !V.getComplexIntImag();
6253 
6254  case APValue::LValue:
6255  return V.isNullPointer();
6256 
6257  case APValue::MemberPointer:
6258  return !V.getMemberPointerDecl();
6259  }
6260 
6261  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled APValue::ValueKind enum");
6262 }
6263 
6264 static QualType getLValueType(ASTContext &Ctx, const APValue &LV) {
6265  QualType T = LV.getLValueBase().getType();
6266  for (APValue::LValuePathEntry E : LV.getLValuePath()) {
6267  if (const ArrayType *AT = Ctx.getAsArrayType(T))
6268  T = AT->getElementType();
6269  else if (const FieldDecl *FD =
6270  dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(E.getAsBaseOrMember().getPointer()))
6271  T = FD->getType();
6272  else
6273  T = Ctx.getRecordType(
6274  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(E.getAsBaseOrMember().getPointer()));
6275  }
6276  return T;
6277 }
6278 
6279 static IdentifierInfo *getUnionInitName(SourceLocation UnionLoc,
6280  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags,
6281  const FieldDecl *FD) {
6282  // According to:
6283  // http://itanium-cxx-abi.github.io/cxx-abi/abi.html#mangling.anonymous
6284  // For the purposes of mangling, the name of an anonymous union is considered
6285  // to be the name of the first named data member found by a pre-order,
6286  // depth-first, declaration-order walk of the data members of the anonymous
6287  // union.
6288 
6289  if (FD->getIdentifier())
6290  return FD->getIdentifier();
6291 
6292  // The only cases where the identifer of a FieldDecl would be blank is if the
6293  // field represents an anonymous record type or if it is an unnamed bitfield.
6294  // There is no type to descend into in the case of a bitfield, so we can just
6295  // return nullptr in that case.
6296  if (FD->isBitField())
6297  return nullptr;
6298  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = FD->getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
6299 
6300  // Consider only the fields in declaration order, searched depth-first. We
6301  // don't care about the active member of the union, as all we are doing is
6302  // looking for a valid name. We also don't check bases, due to guidance from
6303  // the Itanium ABI folks.
6304  for (const FieldDecl *RDField : RD->fields()) {
6305  if (IdentifierInfo *II = getUnionInitName(UnionLoc, Diags, RDField))
6306  return II;
6307  }
6308 
6309  // According to the Itanium ABI: If there is no such data member (i.e., if all
6310  // of the data members in the union are unnamed), then there is no way for a
6311  // program to refer to the anonymous union, and there is therefore no need to
6312  // mangle its name. However, we should diagnose this anyway.
6313  unsigned DiagID = Diags.getCustomDiagID(
6314  DiagnosticsEngine::Error, "cannot mangle this unnamed union NTTP yet");
6315  Diags.Report(UnionLoc, DiagID);
6316 
6317  return nullptr;
6318 }
6319 
6320 void CXXNameMangler::mangleValueInTemplateArg(QualType T, const APValue &V,
6321  bool TopLevel,
6322  bool NeedExactType) {
6323  // Ignore all top-level cv-qualifiers, to match GCC.
6324  Qualifiers Quals;
6325  T = getASTContext().getUnqualifiedArrayType(T, Quals);
6326 
6327  // A top-level expression that's not a primary expression is wrapped in X...E.
6328  bool IsPrimaryExpr = true;
6329  auto NotPrimaryExpr = [&] {
6330  if (TopLevel && IsPrimaryExpr)
6331  Out << 'X';
6332  IsPrimaryExpr = false;
6333  };
6334 
6335  // Proposed in https://github.com/itanium-cxx-abi/cxx-abi/issues/63.
6336  switch (V.getKind()) {
6337  case APValue::None:
6338  case APValue::Indeterminate:
6339  Out << 'L';
6340  mangleType(T);
6341  Out << 'E';
6342  break;
6343 
6344  case APValue::AddrLabelDiff:
6345  llvm_unreachable("unexpected value kind in template argument");
6346 
6347  case APValue::Struct: {
6348  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
6349  assert(RD && "unexpected type for record value");
6350 
6351  // Drop trailing zero-initialized elements.
6352  llvm::SmallVector<const FieldDecl *, 16> Fields(RD->fields());
6353  while (
6354  !Fields.empty() &&
6355  (Fields.back()->isUnnamedBitField() ||
6356  isZeroInitialized(Fields.back()->getType(),
6357  V.getStructField(Fields.back()->getFieldIndex())))) {
6358  Fields.pop_back();
6359  }
6360  llvm::ArrayRef<CXXBaseSpecifier> Bases(RD->bases_begin(), RD->bases_end());
6361  if (Fields.empty()) {
6362  while (!Bases.empty() &&
6363  isZeroInitialized(Bases.back().getType(),
6364  V.getStructBase(Bases.size() - 1)))
6365  Bases = Bases.drop_back();
6366  }
6367 
6368  // <expression> ::= tl <type> <braced-expression>* E
6369  NotPrimaryExpr();
6370  Out << "tl";
6371  mangleType(T);
6372  for (unsigned I = 0, N = Bases.size(); I != N; ++I)
6373  mangleValueInTemplateArg(Bases[I].getType(), V.getStructBase(I), false);
6374  for (unsigned I = 0, N = Fields.size(); I != N; ++I) {
6375  if (Fields[I]->isUnnamedBitField())
6376  continue;
6377  mangleValueInTemplateArg(Fields[I]->getType(),
6378  V.getStructField(Fields[I]->getFieldIndex()),
6379  false);
6380  }
6381  Out << 'E';
6382  break;
6383  }
6384 
6385  case APValue::Union: {
6386  assert(T->getAsCXXRecordDecl() && "unexpected type for union value");
6387  const FieldDecl *FD = V.getUnionField();
6388 
6389  if (!FD) {
6390  Out << 'L';
6391  mangleType(T);
6392  Out << 'E';
6393  break;
6394  }
6395 
6396  // <braced-expression> ::= di <field source-name> <braced-expression>
6397  NotPrimaryExpr();
6398  Out << "tl";
6399  mangleType(T);
6400  if (!isZeroInitialized(T, V)) {
6401  Out << "di";
6402  IdentifierInfo *II = (getUnionInitName(
6403  T->getAsCXXRecordDecl()->getLocation(), Context.getDiags(), FD));
6404  if (II)
6405  mangleSourceName(II);
6406  mangleValueInTemplateArg(FD->getType(), V.getUnionValue(), false);
6407  }
6408  Out << 'E';
6409  break;
6410  }
6411 
6412  case APValue::Array: {
6413  QualType ElemT(T->getArrayElementTypeNoTypeQual(), 0);
6414 
6415  NotPrimaryExpr();
6416  Out << "tl";
6417  mangleType(T);
6418 
6419  // Drop trailing zero-initialized elements.
6420  unsigned N = V.getArraySize();
6421  if (!V.hasArrayFiller() || isZeroInitialized(ElemT, V.getArrayFiller())) {
6422  N = V.getArrayInitializedElts();
6423  while (N && isZeroInitialized(ElemT, V.getArrayInitializedElt(N - 1)))
6424  --N;
6425  }
6426 
6427  for (unsigned I = 0; I != N; ++I) {
6428  const APValue &Elem = I < V.getArrayInitializedElts()
6429  ? V.getArrayInitializedElt(I)
6430  : V.getArrayFiller();
6431  mangleValueInTemplateArg(ElemT, Elem, false);
6432  }
6433  Out << 'E';
6434  break;
6435  }
6436 
6437  case APValue::Vector: {
6438  const VectorType *VT = T->castAs<VectorType>();
6439 
6440  NotPrimaryExpr();
6441  Out << "tl";
6442  mangleType(T);
6443  unsigned N = V.getVectorLength();
6444  while (N && isZeroInitialized(VT->getElementType(), V.getVectorElt(N - 1)))
6445  --N;
6446  for (unsigned I = 0; I != N; ++I)
6447  mangleValueInTemplateArg(VT->getElementType(), V.getVectorElt(I), false);
6448  Out << 'E';
6449  break;
6450  }
6451 
6452  case APValue::Int:
6453  mangleIntegerLiteral(T, V.getInt());
6454  break;
6455 
6456  case APValue::Float:
6457  mangleFloatLiteral(T, V.getFloat());
6458  break;
6459 
6460  case APValue::FixedPoint:
6461  mangleFixedPointLiteral();
6462  break;
6463 
6464  case APValue::ComplexFloat: {
6465  const ComplexType *CT = T->castAs<ComplexType>();
6466  NotPrimaryExpr();
6467  Out << "tl";
6468  mangleType(T);
6469  if (!V.getComplexFloatReal().isPosZero() ||
6470  !V.getComplexFloatImag().isPosZero())
6471  mangleFloatLiteral(CT->getElementType(), V.getComplexFloatReal());
6472  if (!V.getComplexFloatImag().isPosZero())
6473  mangleFloatLiteral(CT->getElementType(), V.getComplexFloatImag());
6474  Out << 'E';
6475  break;
6476  }
6477 
6478  case APValue::ComplexInt: {
6479  const ComplexType *CT = T->castAs<ComplexType>();
6480  NotPrimaryExpr();
6481  Out << "tl";
6482  mangleType(T);
6483  if (V.getComplexIntReal().getBoolValue() ||
6484  V.getComplexIntImag().getBoolValue())
6485  mangleIntegerLiteral(CT->getElementType(), V.getComplexIntReal());
6486  if (V.getComplexIntImag().getBoolValue())
6487  mangleIntegerLiteral(CT->getElementType(), V.getComplexIntImag());
6488  Out << 'E';
6489  break;
6490  }
6491 
6492  case APValue::LValue: {
6493  // Proposed in https://github.com/itanium-cxx-abi/cxx-abi/issues/47.
6494  assert((T->isPointerType() || T->isReferenceType()) &&
6495  "unexpected type for LValue template arg");
6496 
6497  if (V.isNullPointer()) {
6498  mangleNullPointer(T);
6499  break;
6500  }
6501 
6502  APValue::LValueBase B = V.getLValueBase();
6503  if (!B) {
6504  // Non-standard mangling for integer cast to a pointer; this can only
6505  // occur as an extension.
6506  CharUnits Offset = V.getLValueOffset();
6507  if (Offset.isZero()) {
6508  // This is reinterpret_cast<T*>(0), not a null pointer. Mangle this as
6509  // a cast, because L <type> 0 E means something else.
6510  NotPrimaryExpr();
6511  Out << "rc";
6512  mangleType(T);
6513  Out << "Li0E";
6514  if (TopLevel)
6515  Out << 'E';
6516  } else {
6517  Out << "L";
6518  mangleType(T);
6519  Out << Offset.getQuantity() << 'E';
6520  }
6521  break;
6522  }
6523 
6524  ASTContext &Ctx = Context.getASTContext();
6525 
6526  enum { Base, Offset, Path } Kind;
6527  if (!V.hasLValuePath()) {
6528  // Mangle as (T*)((char*)&base + N).
6529  if (T->isReferenceType()) {
6530  NotPrimaryExpr();
6531  Out << "decvP";
6532  mangleType(T->getPointeeType());
6533  } else {
6534  NotPrimaryExpr();
6535  Out << "cv";
6536  mangleType(T);
6537  }
6538  Out << "plcvPcad";
6539  Kind = Offset;
6540  } else {
6541  // Clang 11 and before mangled an array subject to array-to-pointer decay
6542  // as if it were the declaration itself.
6543  bool IsArrayToPointerDecayMangledAsDecl = false;
6544  if (TopLevel && Ctx.getLangOpts().getClangABICompat() <=
6545  LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver11) {
6546  QualType BType = B.getType();
6547  IsArrayToPointerDecayMangledAsDecl =
6548  BType->isArrayType() && V.getLValuePath().size() == 1 &&
6549  V.getLValuePath()[0].getAsArrayIndex() == 0 &&
6550  Ctx.hasSimilarType(T, Ctx.getDecayedType(BType));
6551  }
6552 
6553  if ((!V.getLValuePath().empty() || V.isLValueOnePastTheEnd()) &&
6554  !IsArrayToPointerDecayMangledAsDecl) {
6555  NotPrimaryExpr();
6556  // A final conversion to the template parameter's type is usually
6557  // folded into the 'so' mangling, but we can't do that for 'void*'
6558  // parameters without introducing collisions.
6559  if (NeedExactType && T->isVoidPointerType()) {
6560  Out << "cv";
6561  mangleType(T);
6562  }
6563  if (T->isPointerType())
6564  Out << "ad";
6565  Out << "so";
6566  mangleType(T->isVoidPointerType()
6567  ? getLValueType(Ctx, V).getUnqualifiedType()
6568  : T->getPointeeType());
6569  Kind = Path;
6570  } else {
6571  if (NeedExactType &&
6572  !Ctx.hasSameType(T->getPointeeType(), getLValueType(Ctx, V)) &&
6573  !isCompatibleWith(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver11)) {
6574  NotPrimaryExpr();
6575  Out << "cv";
6576  mangleType(T);
6577  }
6578  if (T->isPointerType()) {
6579  NotPrimaryExpr();
6580  Out << "ad";
6581  }
6582  Kind = Base;
6583  }
6584  }
6585 
6586  QualType TypeSoFar = B.getType();
6587  if (auto *VD = B.dyn_cast<const ValueDecl*>()) {
6588  Out << 'L';
6589  mangle(VD);
6590  Out << 'E';
6591  } else if (auto *E = B.dyn_cast<const Expr*>()) {
6592  NotPrimaryExpr();
6593  mangleExpression(E);
6594  } else if (auto TI = B.dyn_cast<TypeInfoLValue>()) {
6595  NotPrimaryExpr();
6596  Out << "ti";
6597  mangleType(QualType(TI.getType(), 0));
6598  } else {
6599  // We should never see dynamic allocations here.
6600  llvm_unreachable("unexpected lvalue base kind in template argument");
6601  }
6602 
6603  switch (Kind) {
6604  case Base:
6605  break;
6606 
6607  case Offset:
6608  Out << 'L';
6609  mangleType(Ctx.getPointerDiffType());
6610  mangleNumber(V.getLValueOffset().getQuantity());
6611  Out << 'E';
6612  break;
6613 
6614  case Path:
6615  // <expression> ::= so <referent type> <expr> [<offset number>]
6616  // <union-selector>* [p] E
6617  if (!V.getLValueOffset().isZero())
6618  mangleNumber(V.getLValueOffset().getQuantity());
6619 
6620  // We model a past-the-end array pointer as array indexing with index N,
6621  // not with the "past the end" flag. Compensate for that.
6622  bool OnePastTheEnd = V.isLValueOnePastTheEnd();
6623 
6624  for (APValue::LValuePathEntry E : V.getLValuePath()) {
6625  if (auto *AT = TypeSoFar->getAsArrayTypeUnsafe()) {
6626  if (auto *CAT = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT))
6627  OnePastTheEnd |= CAT->getSize() == E.getAsArrayIndex();
6628  TypeSoFar = AT->getElementType();
6629  } else {
6630  const Decl *D = E.getAsBaseOrMember().getPointer();
6631  if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(D)) {
6632  // <union-selector> ::= _ <number>
6633  if (FD->getParent()->isUnion()) {
6634  Out << '_';
6635  if (FD->getFieldIndex())
6636  Out << (FD->getFieldIndex() - 1);
6637  }
6638  TypeSoFar = FD->getType();
6639  } else {
6640  TypeSoFar = Ctx.getRecordType(cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D));
6641  }
6642  }
6643  }
6644 
6645  if (OnePastTheEnd)
6646  Out << 'p';
6647  Out << 'E';
6648  break;
6649  }
6650 
6651  break;
6652  }
6653 
6654  case APValue::MemberPointer:
6655  // Proposed in https://github.com/itanium-cxx-abi/cxx-abi/issues/47.
6656  if (!V.getMemberPointerDecl()) {
6657  mangleNullPointer(T);
6658  break;
6659  }
6660 
6661  ASTContext &Ctx = Context.getASTContext();
6662 
6663  NotPrimaryExpr();
6664  if (!V.getMemberPointerPath().empty()) {
6665  Out << "mc";
6666  mangleType(T);
6667  } else if (NeedExactType &&
6668  !Ctx.hasSameType(
6669  T->castAs<MemberPointerType>()->getPointeeType(),
6670  V.getMemberPointerDecl()->getType()) &&
6671  !isCompatibleWith(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver11)) {
6672  Out << "cv";
6673  mangleType(T);
6674  }
6675  Out << "adL";
6676  mangle(V.getMemberPointerDecl());
6677  Out << 'E';
6678  if (!V.getMemberPointerPath().empty()) {
6679  CharUnits Offset =
6680  Context.getASTContext().getMemberPointerPathAdjustment(V);
6681  if (!Offset.isZero())
6682  mangleNumber(Offset.getQuantity());
6683  Out << 'E';
6684  }
6685  break;
6686  }
6687 
6688  if (TopLevel && !IsPrimaryExpr)
6689  Out << 'E';
6690 }
6691 
6692 void CXXNameMangler::mangleTemplateParameter(unsigned Depth, unsigned Index) {
6693  // <template-param> ::= T_ # first template parameter
6694  // ::= T <parameter-2 non-negative number> _
6695  // ::= TL <L-1 non-negative number> __
6696  // ::= TL <L-1 non-negative number> _
6697  // <parameter-2 non-negative number> _
6698  //
6699  // The latter two manglings are from a proposal here:
6700  // https://github.com/itanium-cxx-abi/cxx-abi/issues/31#issuecomment-528122117
6701  Out << 'T';
6702  Depth += TemplateDepthOffset;
6703  if (Depth != 0)
6704  Out << 'L' << (Depth - 1) << '_';
6705  if (Index != 0)
6706  Out << (Index - 1);
6707  Out << '_';
6708 }
6709 
6710 void CXXNameMangler::mangleSeqID(unsigned SeqID) {
6711  if (SeqID == 0) {
6712  // Nothing.
6713  } else if (SeqID == 1) {
6714  Out << '0';
6715  } else {
6716  SeqID--;
6717 
6718  // <seq-id> is encoded in base-36, using digits and upper case letters.
6719  char Buffer[7]; // log(2**32) / log(36) ~= 7
6720  MutableArrayRef<char> BufferRef(Buffer);
6721  MutableArrayRef<char>::reverse_iterator I = BufferRef.rbegin();
6722 
6723  for (; SeqID != 0; SeqID /= 36) {
6724  unsigned C = SeqID % 36;
6725  *I++ = (C < 10 ? '0' + C : 'A' + C - 10);
6726  }
6727 
6728  Out.write(I.base(), I - BufferRef.rbegin());
6729  }
6730  Out << '_';
6731 }
6732 
6733 void CXXNameMangler::mangleExistingSubstitution(TemplateName tname) {
6734  bool result = mangleSubstitution(tname);
6735  assert(result && "no existing substitution for template name");
6736  (void) result;
6737 }

6739 // <substitution> ::= S <seq-id> _
6740 // ::= S_
6741 bool CXXNameMangler::mangleSubstitution(const NamedDecl *ND) {
6742  // Try one of the standard substitutions first.
6743  if (mangleStandardSubstitution(ND))
6744  return true;
6745 
6746  ND = cast<NamedDecl>(ND->getCanonicalDecl());
6747  return mangleSubstitution(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(ND));
6748 }

6750 bool CXXNameMangler::mangleSubstitution(NestedNameSpecifier *NNS) {
6751  assert(NNS->getKind() == NestedNameSpecifier::Identifier &&
6752  "mangleSubstitution(NestedNameSpecifier *) is only used for "
6753  "identifier nested name specifiers.");
6754  NNS = Context.getASTContext().getCanonicalNestedNameSpecifier(NNS);
6755  return mangleSubstitution(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(NNS));
6756 }

6758 /// Determine whether the given type has any qualifiers that are relevant for
6759 /// substitutions.
6760 static bool hasMangledSubstitutionQualifiers(QualType T) {
6761  Qualifiers Qs = T.getQualifiers();
6762  return Qs.getCVRQualifiers() || Qs.hasAddressSpace() || Qs.hasUnaligned();
6763 }

6765 bool CXXNameMangler::mangleSubstitution(QualType T) {
6766  if (!hasMangledSubstitutionQualifiers(T)) {
6767  if (const RecordType *RT = T->getAs<RecordType>())
6768  return mangleSubstitution(RT->getDecl());
6769  }
6770 
6771  uintptr_t TypePtr = reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(T.getAsOpaquePtr());
6772 
6773  return mangleSubstitution(TypePtr);
6774 }

6777  if (TemplateDecl *TD = Template.getAsTemplateDecl())
6778  return mangleSubstitution(TD);

6781  return mangleSubstitution(
6782  reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(Template.getAsVoidPointer()));
