6785 bool CXXNameMangler::mangleSubstitution(uintptr_t Ptr) {
6786  llvm::DenseMap<uintptr_t, unsigned>::iterator I = Substitutions.find(Ptr);
6787  if (I == Substitutions.end())
6788  return false;
6789 
6790  unsigned SeqID = I->second;
6791  Out << 'S';
6792  mangleSeqID(SeqID);
6793 
6794  return true;
6795 }
6796 
6797 /// Returns whether S is a template specialization of std::Name with a single
6798 /// argument of type A.
6799 bool CXXNameMangler::isSpecializedAs(QualType S, llvm::StringRef Name,
6800  QualType A) {
6801  if (S.isNull())
6802  return false;
6803 
6804  const RecordType *RT = S->getAs<RecordType>();
6805  if (!RT)
6806  return false;
6807 
6808  const ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *SD =
6809  dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RT->getDecl());
6810  if (!SD || !SD->getIdentifier()->isStr(Name))
6811  return false;
6812 
6813  if (!isStdNamespace(Context.getEffectiveDeclContext(SD)))
6814  return false;
6815 
6816  const TemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs = SD->getTemplateArgs();
6817  if (TemplateArgs.size() != 1)
6818  return false;
6819 
6820  if (TemplateArgs[0].getAsType() != A)
6821  return false;
6822 
6823  if (SD->getSpecializedTemplate()->getOwningModuleForLinkage())
6824  return false;
6825 
6826  return true;
6827 }
6828 
6829 /// Returns whether SD is a template specialization std::Name<char,
6830 /// std::char_traits<char> [, std::allocator<char>]>
6831 /// HasAllocator controls whether the 3rd template argument is needed.
6832 bool CXXNameMangler::isStdCharSpecialization(
6833  const ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *SD, llvm::StringRef Name,
6834  bool HasAllocator) {
6835  if (!SD->getIdentifier()->isStr(Name))
6836  return false;
6837 
6838  const TemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs = SD->getTemplateArgs();
6839  if (TemplateArgs.size() != (HasAllocator ? 3 : 2))
6840  return false;
6841 
6842  QualType A = TemplateArgs[0].getAsType();
6843  if (A.isNull())
6844  return false;
6845  // Plain 'char' is named Char_S or Char_U depending on the target ABI.
6846  if (!A->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::Char_S) &&
6847  !A->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::Char_U))
6848  return false;
6849 
6850  if (!isSpecializedAs(TemplateArgs[1].getAsType(), "char_traits", A))
6851  return false;
6852 
6853  if (HasAllocator &&
6854  !isSpecializedAs(TemplateArgs[2].getAsType(), "allocator", A))
6855  return false;
6856 
6857  if (SD->getSpecializedTemplate()->getOwningModuleForLinkage())
6858  return false;
6859 
6860  return true;
6861 }
6862 
6863 bool CXXNameMangler::mangleStandardSubstitution(const NamedDecl *ND) {
6864  // <substitution> ::= St # ::std::
6865  if (const NamespaceDecl *NS = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(ND)) {
6866  if (isStd(NS)) {
6867  Out << "St";
6868  return true;
6869  }
6870  return false;
6871  }
6872 
6873  if (const ClassTemplateDecl *TD = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateDecl>(ND)) {
6874  if (!isStdNamespace(Context.getEffectiveDeclContext(TD)))
6875  return false;
6876 
6877  if (TD->getOwningModuleForLinkage())
6878  return false;
6879 
6880  // <substitution> ::= Sa # ::std::allocator
6881  if (TD->getIdentifier()->isStr("allocator")) {
6882  Out << "Sa";
6883  return true;
6884  }
6885 
6886  // <<substitution> ::= Sb # ::std::basic_string
6887  if (TD->getIdentifier()->isStr("basic_string")) {
6888  Out << "Sb";
6889  return true;
6890  }
6891  return false;
6892  }
6893 
6894  if (const ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *SD =
6895  dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(ND)) {
6896  if (!isStdNamespace(Context.getEffectiveDeclContext(SD)))
6897  return false;
6898 
6899  if (SD->getSpecializedTemplate()->getOwningModuleForLinkage())
6900  return false;
6901 
6902  // <substitution> ::= Ss # ::std::basic_string<char,
6903  // ::std::char_traits<char>,
6904  // ::std::allocator<char> >
6905  if (isStdCharSpecialization(SD, "basic_string", /*HasAllocator=*/true)) {
6906  Out << "Ss";
6907  return true;
6908  }
6909 
6910  // <substitution> ::= Si # ::std::basic_istream<char,
6911  // ::std::char_traits<char> >
6912  if (isStdCharSpecialization(SD, "basic_istream", /*HasAllocator=*/false)) {
6913  Out << "Si";
6914  return true;
6915  }
6916 
6917  // <substitution> ::= So # ::std::basic_ostream<char,
6918  // ::std::char_traits<char> >
6919  if (isStdCharSpecialization(SD, "basic_ostream", /*HasAllocator=*/false)) {
6920  Out << "So";
6921  return true;
6922  }
6923 
6924  // <substitution> ::= Sd # ::std::basic_iostream<char,
6925  // ::std::char_traits<char> >
6926  if (isStdCharSpecialization(SD, "basic_iostream", /*HasAllocator=*/false)) {
6927  Out << "Sd";
6928  return true;
6929  }
6930  return false;
6931  }
6932 
6933  return false;
6934 }
6935 
6936 void CXXNameMangler::addSubstitution(QualType T) {
6937  if (!hasMangledSubstitutionQualifiers(T)) {
6938  if (const RecordType *RT = T->getAs<RecordType>()) {
6939  addSubstitution(RT->getDecl());
6940  return;
6941  }
6942  }
6943 
6944  uintptr_t TypePtr = reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(T.getAsOpaquePtr());
6945  addSubstitution(TypePtr);
6946 }
6947 
6948 void CXXNameMangler::addSubstitution(TemplateName Template) {
6949  if (TemplateDecl *TD = Template.getAsTemplateDecl())
6950  return addSubstitution(TD);
6951 
6952  Template = Context.getASTContext().getCanonicalTemplateName(Template);
6953  addSubstitution(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(Template.getAsVoidPointer()));
6954 }

6956 void CXXNameMangler::addSubstitution(uintptr_t Ptr) {
6957  assert(!Substitutions.count(Ptr) && "Substitution already exists!");
6958  Substitutions[Ptr] = SeqID++;
6959 }
6960 
6961 void CXXNameMangler::extendSubstitutions(CXXNameMangler* Other) {
6962  assert(Other->SeqID >= SeqID && "Must be superset of substitutions!");
6963  if (Other->SeqID > SeqID) {
6964  Substitutions.swap(Other->Substitutions);
6965  SeqID = Other->SeqID;
6966  }
6967 }

6969 CXXNameMangler::AbiTagList
6970 CXXNameMangler::makeFunctionReturnTypeTags(const FunctionDecl *FD) {
6971  // When derived abi tags are disabled there is no need to make any list.
6972  if (DisableDerivedAbiTags)
6973  return AbiTagList();
6974 
6975  llvm::raw_null_ostream NullOutStream;
6976  CXXNameMangler TrackReturnTypeTags(*this, NullOutStream);
6977  TrackReturnTypeTags.disableDerivedAbiTags();
6978 
6979  const FunctionProtoType *Proto =
6980  cast<FunctionProtoType>(FD->getType()->getAs<FunctionType>());
6981  FunctionTypeDepthState saved = TrackReturnTypeTags.FunctionTypeDepth.push();
6982  TrackReturnTypeTags.FunctionTypeDepth.enterResultType();
6983  TrackReturnTypeTags.mangleType(Proto->getReturnType());
6984  TrackReturnTypeTags.FunctionTypeDepth.leaveResultType();
6985  TrackReturnTypeTags.FunctionTypeDepth.pop(saved);
6986 
6987  return TrackReturnTypeTags.AbiTagsRoot.getSortedUniqueUsedAbiTags();
6988 }

6990 CXXNameMangler::AbiTagList
6991 CXXNameMangler::makeVariableTypeTags(const VarDecl *VD) {
6992  // When derived abi tags are disabled there is no need to make any list.
6993  if (DisableDerivedAbiTags)
6994  return AbiTagList();
6995 
6996  llvm::raw_null_ostream NullOutStream;
6997  CXXNameMangler TrackVariableType(*this, NullOutStream);
6998  TrackVariableType.disableDerivedAbiTags();
6999 
7000  TrackVariableType.mangleType(VD->getType());
7001 
7002  return TrackVariableType.AbiTagsRoot.getSortedUniqueUsedAbiTags();
7003 }

7005 bool CXXNameMangler::shouldHaveAbiTags(ItaniumMangleContextImpl &C,
7006  const VarDecl *VD) {

7013 //
7014 
7015 /// Mangles the name of the declaration D and emits that name to the given
7016 /// output stream.
7017 ///
7018 /// If the declaration D requires a mangled name, this routine will emit that
7019 /// mangled name to \p os and return true. Otherwise, \p os will be unchanged
7020 /// and this routine will return false. In this case, the caller should just
7021 /// emit the identifier of the declaration (\c D->getIdentifier()) as its
7022 /// name.
7023 void ItaniumMangleContextImpl::mangleCXXName(GlobalDecl GD,
7024  raw_ostream &Out) {
7025  const NamedDecl *D = cast<NamedDecl>(GD.getDecl());
7026  assert((isa<FunctionDecl, VarDecl, TemplateParamObjectDecl>(D)) &&
7027  "Invalid mangleName() call, argument is not a variable or function!");
7028 
7029  PrettyStackTraceDecl CrashInfo(D, SourceLocation(),
7030  getASTContext().getSourceManager(),
7031  "Mangling declaration");
7032 
7033  if (auto *CD = dyn_cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(D)) {
7034  auto Type = GD.getCtorType();
7035  CXXNameMangler Mangler(*this, Out, CD, Type);
7036  return Mangler.mangle(GlobalDecl(CD, Type));
7037  }
7038 
7039  if (auto *DD = dyn_cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(D)) {
7040  auto Type = GD.getDtorType();
7041  CXXNameMangler Mangler(*this, Out, DD, Type);
7042  return Mangler.mangle(GlobalDecl(DD, Type));
7043  }
7044 
7045  CXXNameMangler Mangler(*this, Out, D);
7046  Mangler.mangle(GD);
7047 }
7048 
7049 void ItaniumMangleContextImpl::mangleCXXCtorComdat(const CXXConstructorDecl *D,
7050  raw_ostream &Out) {
7051  CXXNameMangler Mangler(*this, Out, D, Ctor_Comdat);
7052  Mangler.mangle(GlobalDecl(D, Ctor_Comdat));
7053 }
7054 
7055 void ItaniumMangleContextImpl::mangleCXXDtorComdat(const CXXDestructorDecl *D,
7056  raw_ostream &Out) {
7057  CXXNameMangler Mangler(*this, Out, D, Dtor_Comdat);
7058  Mangler.mangle(GlobalDecl(D, Dtor_Comdat));
7059 }
7060 
7061 void ItaniumMangleContextImpl::mangleThunk(const CXXMethodDecl *MD,
7062  const ThunkInfo &Thunk,
7063  raw_ostream &Out) {
7064  // <special-name> ::= T <call-offset> <base encoding>
7065  // # base is the nominal target function of thunk
7066  // <special-name> ::= Tc <call-offset> <call-offset> <base encoding>
7067  // # base is the nominal target function of thunk
7068  // # first call-offset is 'this' adjustment
7069  // # second call-offset is result adjustment
7070 
7071  assert(!isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(MD) &&
7072  "Use mangleCXXDtor for destructor decls!");
7073  CXXNameMangler Mangler(*this, Out);
7074  Mangler.getStream() << "_ZT";
7075  if (!Thunk.Return.isEmpty())
7076  Mangler.getStream() << 'c';
7077 
7078  // Mangle the 'this' pointer adjustment.
7079  Mangler.mangleCallOffset(Thunk.This.NonVirtual,
7080  Thunk.This.Virtual.Itanium.VCallOffsetOffset);
7081 
7082  // Mangle the return pointer adjustment if there is one.
7083  if (!Thunk.Return.isEmpty())
7084  Mangler.mangleCallOffset(Thunk.Return.NonVirtual,
7085  Thunk.Return.Virtual.Itanium.VBaseOffsetOffset);
7086 
7087  Mangler.mangleFunctionEncoding(MD);
7088 }
7089 
7090 void ItaniumMangleContextImpl::mangleCXXDtorThunk(
7091  const CXXDestructorDecl *DD, CXXDtorType Type,
7092  const ThisAdjustment &ThisAdjustment, raw_ostream &Out) {
7093  // <special-name> ::= T <call-offset> <base encoding>
7094  // # base is the nominal target function of thunk
7095  CXXNameMangler Mangler(*this, Out, DD, Type);
7096  Mangler.getStream() << "_ZT";
7097 
7098  // Mangle the 'this' pointer adjustment.
7099  Mangler.mangleCallOffset(ThisAdjustment.NonVirtual,
7100  ThisAdjustment.Virtual.Itanium.VCallOffsetOffset);
7101 
7102  Mangler.mangleFunctionEncoding(GlobalDecl(DD, Type));
7103 }

7105 /// Returns the mangled name for a guard variable for the passed in VarDecl.
7106 void ItaniumMangleContextImpl::mangleStaticGuardVariable(const VarDecl *D,
7107  raw_ostream &Out) {
7108  // <special-name> ::= GV <object name> # Guard variable for one-time
7109  // # initialization
7110  CXXNameMangler Mangler(*this, Out);
7111  // GCC 5.3.0 doesn't emit derived ABI tags for local names but that seems to
7112  // be a bug that is fixed in trunk.
7113  Mangler.getStream() << "_ZGV";
7114  Mangler.mangleName(D);
7115 }

7159 void ItaniumMangleContextImpl::mangleSEHFinallyBlock(
7160  GlobalDecl EnclosingDecl, raw_ostream &Out) {
7161  CXXNameMangler Mangler(*this, Out);
7162  Mangler.getStream() << "__fin_";
7163  auto *EnclosingFD = cast<FunctionDecl>(EnclosingDecl.getDecl());
7164  if (shouldMangleDeclName(EnclosingFD))
7165  Mangler.mangle(EnclosingDecl);
7166  else
7167  Mangler.getStream() << EnclosingFD->getName();
7168 }
7169 
7170 void ItaniumMangleContextImpl::mangleItaniumThreadLocalInit(const VarDecl *D,
7171  raw_ostream &Out) {
7172  // <special-name> ::= TH <object name>
7173  CXXNameMangler Mangler(*this, Out);
7174  Mangler.getStream() << "_ZTH";
7175  Mangler.mangleName(D);
7176 }
7177 
7178 void
7179 ItaniumMangleContextImpl::mangleItaniumThreadLocalWrapper(const VarDecl *D,
7180  raw_ostream &Out) {
7181  // <special-name> ::= TW <object name>
7182  CXXNameMangler Mangler(*this, Out);
7183  Mangler.getStream() << "_ZTW";
7184  Mangler.mangleName(D);
7185 }
7186 
7187 void ItaniumMangleContextImpl::mangleReferenceTemporary(const VarDecl *D,
7188  unsigned ManglingNumber,
7189  raw_ostream &Out) {
7190  // We match the GCC mangling here.
7191  // <special-name> ::= GR <object name>
7192  CXXNameMangler Mangler(*this, Out);
7193  Mangler.getStream() << "_ZGR";
7194  Mangler.mangleName(D);
7195  assert(ManglingNumber > 0 && "Reference temporary mangling number is zero!");
7196  Mangler.mangleSeqID(ManglingNumber - 1);
7197 }

7215 void ItaniumMangleContextImpl::mangleCXXCtorVTable(const CXXRecordDecl *RD,
7216  int64_t Offset,
7217  const CXXRecordDecl *Type,
7218  raw_ostream &Out) {
7219  // <special-name> ::= TC <type> <offset number> _ <base type>
7220  CXXNameMangler Mangler(*this, Out);
7221  Mangler.getStream() << "_ZTC";
7222  Mangler.mangleNameOrStandardSubstitution(RD);
7223  Mangler.getStream() << Offset;
7224  Mangler.getStream() << '_';
7225  Mangler.mangleNameOrStandardSubstitution(Type);
7226 }

7228 void ItaniumMangleContextImpl::mangleCXXRTTI(QualType Ty, raw_ostream &Out) {
7229  // <special-name> ::= TI <type> # typeinfo structure
7230  assert(!Ty.hasQualifiers() && "RTTI info cannot have top-level qualifiers");
7231  CXXNameMangler Mangler(*this, Out);
7232  Mangler.getStream() << "_ZTI";
7233  Mangler.mangleType(Ty);
7234 }

7258 
7259 void ItaniumMangleContextImpl::mangleModuleInitializer(const Module *M,
7260  raw_ostream &Out) {
7261  // <special-name> ::= GI <module-name> # module initializer function
7262  CXXNameMangler Mangler(*this, Out);
7263  Mangler.getStream() << "_ZGI";
7264  Mangler.mangleModuleNamePrefix(M->getPrimaryModuleInterfaceName());
7265  if (M->isModulePartition()) {
7266  // The partition needs including, as partitions can have them too.
7267  auto Partition = M->Name.find(':');
7268  Mangler.mangleModuleNamePrefix(
7269  StringRef(&M->Name[Partition + 1], M->Name.size() - Partition - 1),
7270  /*IsPartition*/ true);
7271  }
7272 }

7274 ItaniumMangleContext *ItaniumMangleContext::create(ASTContext &Context,
7275  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags,
7276  bool IsAux) {
7277  return new ItaniumMangleContextImpl(
7278  Context, Diags,
7279  [](ASTContext &, const NamedDecl *) -> std::optional<unsigned> {
7280  return std::nullopt;
7281  },
7282  IsAux);
7283 }
